1
00:02:15,816 --> 00:02:18,141
Call me Ishmael.
叫我以赛马利

2
00:02:47,444 --> 00:02:49,982
Some years ago,
having little or no money...
几年前我几乎身无分文……

3
00:02:50,155 --> 00:02:53,405
I thought I would sail about
and see the oceans of the world.
我想我应该出海去看看世界

4
00:02:53,491 --> 00:02:55,898
Whenever I get grim and spleenful...
当我心情沮丧脾气糟糕的时候……

5
00:02:55,993 --> 00:02:59,576
whenever I feel like
knocking people 's hats off in the street...
当我看街上的人都不顺眼的时候……

6
00:02:59,663 --> 00:03:02,949
whenever it's a damp,
drizzly November in my soul...
当我的心里像潮湿多雨的11月的时候……

7
00:03:03,041 --> 00:03:06,161
I know that it's high time
to get to sea again.
我知道又到了立刻出海的时候了

8
00:03:06,253 --> 00:03:08,922
Choose any path you please...
随意选一条航线……

9
00:03:09,005 --> 00:03:11,674
and ten to one,
it carries you down to water.
十有八九它会把你带到水里

10
00:03:12,008 --> 00:03:15,423
There 's a magic in water
that draws all men away from the land...
海水有一种魔力，可以吸引所有的男人们离开陆地……

11
00:03:15,511 --> 00:03:19,971
Leads them over the hills down creeks,
and streams, and rivers to the sea.
引领他们越过山川,小溪,山涧与河流,最终到达大海

12
00:03:23,060 --> 00:03:24,257
The sea...
面对大海……

13
00:03:24,352 --> 00:03:28,101
where each man, as in a mirror,
finds himself.
每个男人都可以像照镜子一样，找回自我

14
00:03:31,359 --> 00:03:34,692
And so it was
I duly arrived at the town of New Bedford...
确实如此，1841年的一个风雨交加的周六晚上

15
00:03:34,820 --> 00:03:38,864
on a stormy Saturday late in the year 184 1.
我按时来到了新贝德福德这个小镇…

16
00:04:31,804 --> 00:04:34,046
-Rum. 朗姆酒
-Rum it is. What mark? 朗姆酒是吧，用哪种喝法？

17
00:04:34,140 --> 00:04:37,674
To this a penny, to that another penny, and so on to the top of the glass.
到这是一便士 到这是两便士 就这样直到杯子倒满

18
00:04:37,768 --> 00:04:40,935
The Cape Horn measure, which
you may drink down for a full shilling.
如果用合恩角的喝法，你可以一先令一先令地喝

19
00:04:41,021 --> 00:04:43,512
The penny mark. Nay, the full shilling.
便士记号， 不，来一先令的

20
00:04:45,442 --> 00:04:47,518
You'll be wanting a room tonight.
你今晚需要个房间吧

21
00:04:48,319 --> 00:04:52,483
You ain't no objections to sharing
a harpooneer's bed with him, have you?
你对和鱼叉手共睡一张床没有意见吧？

22
00:04:52,573 --> 00:04:54,981
-You going whaling?  你是去捕鲸吗？
-That is my intention.  有这个打算

23
00:04:55,075 --> 00:04:58,574
You need permission. You weren't born and bred in New Bedford,
were you?
你需要许可证，你不是在新贝德福德出生长大的吧？

24
00:04:58,662 --> 00:04:59,990
No, I'm a stranger here.
不是，我是个外地人

25
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:02,535
-Then you'll have to have permission.  那你需要许可证
-Permission?   许可证？

26
00:05:02,624 --> 00:05:06,538
Aye. From us, the men of New Bedford.
The sea is ours. 
是的。由我们新贝德福德的人颁发的许可证
这片海是我们的。

27
00:05:06,628 --> 00:05:08,953
Other seamen only have
a right of way through it.
其他海员水手只有通过的权利。

28
00:05:09,046 --> 00:05:11,537
And the whale is ours. Ours alone.
鲸鱼也是我们的，只属于我们

29
00:05:11,632 --> 00:05:15,297
