Who no speak? I kill you!
不说话是吗？ 小心我杀了你！

88
00:09:47,805 --> 00:09:48,968
Landlord!
老板！

89
00:09:49,056 --> 00:09:52,010
Peter Coffin! Coffin, save me!
Peter Coffin！ 
彼得.考芬 救救我！

90
00:09:52,101 --> 00:09:53,761
Now, now, now.
来了，来了

91
00:09:53,977 --> 00:09:55,886
What is all this about?
这是怎么回事？

92
00:09:57,355 --> 00:10:00,190
Why didn't you tell me
I was sleeping with a cannibal?
你怎么没告诉我要和一个食人族一起睡？

93
00:10:00,275 --> 00:10:01,733
I thought you knowed.
我以为你知道的

94
00:10:01,818 --> 00:10:04,937
Didn't I tell you
he was around the town selling heads?
我没告诉你他在这阵子附近卖人头吗？

95
00:10:05,071 --> 00:10:09,649
Landlord, tell him to stash that tomahawk,
or pipe, or whatever you call it.
老板，让他把那个战斧还是烟斗什么的玩意收好

96
00:10:19,792 --> 00:10:21,951
Well, pleasant dreams.
好的，晚安

97
00:10:33,054 --> 00:10:35,841
Better a sober cannibal
than a drunken Christian.
一个清醒的食人族好过一个烂醉的基督徒

98
00:10:39,352 --> 00:10:43,219
In this same New Bedford,
there stands a Whaleman 's Chapel...
就在这个新贝德福德镇上， 有一个属于捕鲸者的小教堂……

99
00:10:43,564 --> 00:10:47,941
and few are the fishermen shortly bound for the Indian Ocean or Pacific...
那些短期内出发前往印度洋的渔民们……

100
00:10:48,110 --> 00:10:50,067
who fail to visit there.
几乎没有人不去那里

101
00:10:53,490 --> 00:10:59,341
The will of God I did deny
我否认了上帝的旨意

102
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:05,674
And so my sacred duty fled
逃避了我神圣的职责

103
00:11:06,351 --> 00:11:11,807
Oh, my Lord's awful penalty
哦，上帝的惩罚太可怕了

104
00:11:11,981 --> 00:11:18,101
Is not to die and yet be dead
不仅是死去和等死

105
00:11:19,029 --> 00:11:25,031
The ribs and terrors in the whale
鲸鱼的肋骨和恐怖

106
00:11:25,618 --> 00:11:31,620
Arched over me a dismal gloom
在我身上形成了阴森的阴影

107
00:11:32,249 --> 00:11:38,121
While all God's sun-lit waves rolled by
当所有上帝照耀的波浪滚滚而过

108
00:11:38,380 --> 00:11:44,382
And lift me deepening down to doom
把我带到更深的厄运之中

109
00:11:45,386 --> 00:11:51,388
I saw the opening maw of hell
我看到地狱之门打开

110
00:11:51,767 --> 00:11:57,721
With endless pains and sorrows there
那里有无尽的痛苦和悲伤

111
00:11:58,398 --> 00:12:04,103
Which none but they that feel can tell
只有经历过的人才能描述

112
00:12:04,403 --> 00:12:10,405
Oh, I was plunging to despair
哦，正当我要陷入绝望之中

113
00:12:11,409 --> 00:12:17,412
In black distress, I called my God
在黑暗的痛苦中，我呼唤我的上帝

114
00:12:18,249 --> 00:12:24,251
When I could scarce believe him mine
当我几乎不能相信他的时候

115
00:12:25,172 --> 00:12:30,960
He bowed his ear to my complaints
他侧耳倾听了我的抱怨

116
00:12:31,261 --> 00:12:35,175
No more the whale
我不要再把

117
00:12:35,264 --> 00:12:40,523
Did me confine
鲸鱼关起来

118
00:12:41,953 --> 00:12:46,947
Amen
阿门

119
00:12:58,134 --> 00:13:01,218
"And God had prepared a great fish...
“上帝安排了一条大鱼……

120
00:13:01,929 --> 00:13:03,839
"to swallow up Jonah."
要吞掉约拿“

121
00:13:05,975 --> 00:13:07,220
Shipmates...
船友们……

122
00:13:08,143 --> 00:13:09,887
the sin of Jonah...
约拿的罪

123
00:13:10,062 --> 00:13:12,683
was in his disobedience of the command of God.
是他不顺服从神的旨意

124
00:13:12,773 --> 00:13:14,730
He found it a hard command.
他觉得这命令太难了

125
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:16,775
And it was, shipmates...
是的，船友们……

126
00:13:16,860 --> 00:13:19,896
for all the things that God would have us do are hard.
因为神要我们做的一切事都是难的

127
00:13:20,530 --> 00:13:24,112
If we would obey God, we must disobey ourselves.
我们若要顺服神，就必须违背自己。

128
00:13:24,325 --> 00:13:29,033
But Jonah still further flouts at God by seeking to flee
from him.
可是约拿试图逃跑，这是对上帝的进一步不敬

129
00:13:29,705 --> 00:13:32,871
Jonah thinks that a ship made by men...
约拿以为人类造的船

130
00:13:32,958 --> 00:13:36,409
will carry him into countries where God does not reign.
会把他带到没有上帝统治的国度

131
00:13:37,378 --> 00:13:39,750
He prowls among the shipping...
他在船只之间徘徊……

132
00:13:39,839 --> 00:13:43,587
Like a vile burglar,
hastening to cross the seas.
像一个卑鄙的窃贼一样，急着要出海

133
00:13:44,051 --> 00:13:47,716
And as he comes aboard,
the sailors mark him.
当他上船时，水手们在他身上做记号

134
00:13:49,598 --> 00:13:51,257
The ship puts out...
船出发了

135
00:13:52,350 --> 00:13:56,264
but soon the sea rebels.
It will not bear the wicked burden.
但是很快大海反抗了起来，它不能容忍这个邪恶的负担

136
00:13:56,854 --> 00:13:59,641
A dreadful storm comes up.
The ship is like to break.
一场可怕的暴风雨来了，而船好像就要沉了

137
00:13:59,732 --> 00:14:01,938
The boatswain calls
all hands to lighten her.
水手长发动所有人来减轻船的重量

138
00:14:02,026 --> 00:14:05,726
Boxes, bales, and jars are clattering
overboard.
箱子，包裹，和罐子被稀里哗啦的地到海里

139
00:14:05,821 --> 00:14:08,691
The wind is shrieking. The men are yelling.
狂风在咆哮，人们在尖叫

140
00:14:08,907 --> 00:14:11,232
"l fear the Lord," cries Jonah...
“我敬畏上帝”，约拿喊道

141
00:14:11,326 --> 00:14:15,370
"the God of heaven,
who hath made the sea and the dry land."
“天上的神，他创造了大海和旱地”

142
00:14:18,249 --> 00:14:20,838
Again, the sailors mark him.
水手们又给他做了记号

143
00:14:22,143 --> 00:14:26,437
But wretched Jonah cries out to them
to cast him overboard...
但是可怜的约拿呼喊着要他们把他扔到海里

144
00:14:26,814 --> 00:14:30,977
for he knew that for his sake
this great tempest was upon them.
因为他知道这场风暴是冲着他来的

145
00:14:32,152 --> 00:14:33,777
Now behold Jonah...
现在看看约拿啊……

146
00:14:34,279 --> 00:14:38,490
taken up as an anchor
and dropped into the sea...
被当做锚丢到海里……

147
00:14:40,034 --> 00:14:43,284
into the dreadful jaws awaiting him.
丢到等待已久的血盆大口之中

148
00:14:44,663 --> 00:14:48,447
And the great whale shoots
to all his ivory teeth...
而鲸鱼竖起它象牙般的利齿

149
00:14:49,168 --> 00:14:53,628
Like so many white bolts upon his prison.
就像牢房里到处都是的白色栅栏

150
00:14:55,507 --> 00:14:58,710
And Jonah cries unto the Lord...
约拿在鱼腹中

151
00:14:59,052 --> 00:15:01,127
out of the fish's belly.
求告耶和华

152
00:15:02,805 --> 00:15:05,047
Nut observe his prayer, shipmates.
但是请注意他的祈祷，船友们。

153
00:15:05,849 --> 00:15:07,641
He doesn't weep and wail.
他没有哭泣或悲叹

154
00:15:07,726 --> 00:15:12,020
He feels his punishment is just.
He leaves deliverance to God.
他觉得对他的惩罚是公正的，他把自己交给上帝处置

155
00:15:12,939 --> 00:15:15,264
And even out of the belly of hell...
甚至是在地狱的肚子里

156
00:15:16,067 --> 00:15:19,601
grounded upon the ocean's utmost bones...
大海的最深处

157
00:15:20,446 --> 00:15:22,569
God heard him when he cried.
上帝还是听到了他的喊叫

158
00:15:23,615 --> 00:15:25,691
And God spake unto the whale.
上帝对鲸鱼做了吩咐

159
00:15:27,077 --> 00:15:30,243
And from the shuddering cold
and blackness of the deep...
鲸鱼突然从深海的冰冷和黑暗之中

160
00:15:30,330 --> 00:15:33,034
the whale breached into the sun...
冲到了阳光下……

161
00:15:33,791 --> 00:15:36,875
and vomited out Jonah upon the dry land.
把约拿吐出来落到了陆地上

162
00:15:38,838 --> 00:15:40,213
And Jonah...
而约拿浑身

163
00:15:41,298 --> 00:15:43,089
bruised and beaten...
青一块紫一块

164
00:15:44,468 --> 00:15:47,634
his ears like two seashells...
他的耳朵像两片贝壳一样……

165
00:15:48,304 --> 00:15:52,516
still multitudinously murmuring
of the ocean...
还一直回响着大海的声音

166
00:15:53,643 --> 00:15:55,801
Jonah did the Almighty's bidding.
约拿听从了全能者的吩咐

167
00:15:55,895 --> 00:15:57,804
And what was that, shipmates?
那是什么，船友们？

168
00:15:58,731 --> 00:16:02,791
To preach the truth
in the face of falsehood!
在谎言面前宣扬真理!

169
00:16:03,626 --> 00:16:07,291
No, shipmates. Woe to him who seeks
to pour oil on the troubled waters...
不，船友们。那些想在浑水上浇油的有祸了，

170
00:16:07,379 --> 00:16:09,953
when God has brewed them into a gale.
因为神已经把浑水化作狂风

171
00:16:10,841 --> 00:16:14,838
Yea, woe to him who,
as the pilot Paul has it...
那像领航的保罗一样传道给人听的，

172
00:16:15,512 --> 00:16:20,138
while preaching to others
is himself a castaway.
自己却被弃绝了的，有祸了


173
00:16:23,144 --> 00:16:26,144
Delight is to him...
而那些

174
00:16:27,523 --> 00:16:31,935
who, against the proud gods
and commodores of this earth...
凡与世上狂傲的神和同伴相争

175
00:16:34,028 --> 00:16:36,863
stands forth his own inexorable self...
彰显自己刚强之心的，便为有福

176
00:16:38,074 --> 00:16:41,442
who destroys all sin
though he pluck it out...
虽然他从元老院和法官的袍子底下把罪都拔出来

177
00:16:41,535 --> 00:16:45,402
from under the robes
of senators and judges!
却把一切罪都消灭了的，便为有福

178
00:16:47,916 --> 00:16:50,454
And eternal delight shall be his...
而来躺下的人，

179
00:16:51,628 --> 00:16:54,119
who, coming to lay him down, can say:
他必永远喜乐，并说：

180
00:16:56,799 --> 00:16:58,210
"O Father...
噢，天父

181
00:16:59,301 --> 00:17:01,294
"mortal or immortal...
无论我是凡人还是神仙

182
00:17:02,554 --> 00:17:03,835
"here I die.
我都会在这里死去

183
00:17:06,892 --> 00:17:08,884
"l have striven to be thine...
我已经努力让自己属于你

184
00:17:10,061 --> 00:17:12,219
"more than to be this world's...
胜过属于这个世界

185
00:17:13,356 --> 00:17:14,814
"or mine own.
或是我自己

186
00:17:16,108 --> 00:17:17,602
"Yet this is nothing.
然而这不算什么

187
00:17:19,069 --> 00:17:21,394
"l leave eternity to thee.
我把永恒留给你

188
00:17:23,198 --> 00:17:24,941
"For what is man...
人算什么

189
00:17:26,409 --> 00:17:29,576
"that he should live out
the lifetime of his God?"
怎么能和神共生死呢？"

190
00:17:47,778 --> 00:17:49,058
And 50.
第50页

191
00:17:50,697 --> 00:17:52,820
Three time I count 50.
我用了三次数到了50页

192
00:17:54,492 --> 00:17:56,117
Many pages, many.
太多页了，太多页

193
00:17:57,453 --> 00:17:58,782
A big book.
一本大厚书

194
00:17:59,539 --> 00:18:01,116
You know words?
你识字吗？

195
00:18:02,625 --> 00:18:05,294
I know picture. This whale.
我认得这幅画，这条鲸鱼

196
00:18:05,961 --> 00:18:07,538
You speak words.
你帮我读一下文字部分

197
00:18:08,005 --> 00:18:10,044
"The heart of the whale is larger...
“鲸鱼的心脏

198
00:18:10,131 --> 00:18:12,966
"than the pipe of the waterworks
at London Bridge.
比伦敦桥自来水厂的水管还要粗大

199
00:18:13,051 --> 00:18:16,633
"The water in that pipe
is not so thick or fast...
水管里的水流的密度和速度

200
00:18:17,138 --> 00:18:19,593
"as the blood pumping
from the heart of the whale."
还赶不上鲸鱼心脏里血液的循环

201
00:18:19,682 --> 00:18:21,923
True. Thank you.
是真的，谢谢你

202
00:18:23,769 --> 00:18:25,097
Queequeg...
魁魁格……

203
00:18:26,146 --> 00:18:28,719
who are you? Where are you from?
你是谁，你从哪来？

204
00:18:29,649 --> 00:18:32,104
My father king. I chief.
我父亲是国王，我是酋长

205
00:18:32,819 --> 00:18:35,107
My uncle a high priest in islands...
我叔叔是遥远的西南方

206
00:18:36,155 --> 00:18:38,231
west south far away.
岛屿上的大祭司

207
00:18:38,908 --> 00:18:40,567
Ship come by island.
船只从岛屿旁经过

208
00:18:41,034 --> 00:18:44,237
I take canoe, I sail, I swim...
我做了条独木舟划过去，然后再游泳

209
00:18:44,579 --> 00:18:46,655
I climb rope, I hide.
顺着绳子爬上船，藏起来

210
00:18:47,332 --> 00:18:50,286
Ship take me far. Many years.
船把我带到远方，很多年

211
00:18:50,877 --> 00:18:52,750
See all world.
环游世界

212
00:18:53,713 --> 00:18:58,208
Odd. Many is the Christian wishes
he was a dark man on a cannibal isle.
奇怪，很多基督徒都希望他是个深色皮肤的食人族

213
00:18:59,968 --> 00:19:02,803
-What next, Queequeg?  下一步做什么，魁魁格？
-Sail ship. You? 出海，你呢？

214
00:19:02,888 --> 00:19:05,758
Tomorrow I hope to sign aboard any ship
in search of whales.
明天我希望能随便上一搜捕鲸船

215
00:19:05,849 --> 00:19:08,635
I sign, too. Your boat, my boat.
我也去，你上哪艘船，我就上那艘船

216
00:19:08,893 --> 00:19:12,262
I eat same food. We sail on same waters.
我们同吃同住，一起航海

217
00:19:12,605 --> 00:19:14,514
We kill same whale.
我们一起捕鲸

218
00:19:15,107 --> 00:19:16,482
We friends.
我们是朋友

219
00:19:16,692 --> 00:19:20,207
Same blood, same head, all same.
同样的血液，同样的头，都一样

220
00:19:23,214 --> 00:19:25,336
Well, which will it be, Queequeg?
那，选哪一条船呢，魁魁格？

221
00:19:25,716 --> 00:19:28,041
The Tit-bit? Not a bad ship.
珍品号，这艘船不赖

222
00:19:29,052 --> 00:19:31,424
What do you say to the Devil-dam?
你觉得 恶魔大坝 怎么样？

223
00:19:32,055 --> 00:19:33,217
Pequod.
裴廓德号

224
00:19:35,224 --> 00:19:36,884
Well, now.
好，来吧

225
00:19:39,979 --> 00:19:41,852
Look at the ivory she's wearing.
瞧她上面这些象牙啊

226
00:19:41,939 --> 00:19:44,477
She's all tricked out
in the bones of her victims.
她周身都用战利品的骨头作为装饰

227
00:19:44,566 --> 00:19:47,187
Those cleats made from whale's teeth.
那些楔子都是鲸鱼的牙做的

228
00:19:47,402 --> 00:19:50,901
And the tiller, Queequeg,
it's carved from a whale's jaw.
还有这舵柄，魁魁格，是用鲸鱼的颚骨雕刻出来的

229
00:19:58,579 --> 00:20:00,951
Ahoy there! Someone aboard?
喂，有人上船吗？

230
00:20:01,623 --> 00:20:03,746
Is this the captain of the Pequod?
你是裴廓德号的船长吗？

231
00:20:04,084 --> 00:20:06,539
What doest thee want of the captain?
你们想要见船长干什么？

232
00:20:06,962 --> 00:20:08,456
We were thinking of shipping.
我们想要出海

233
00:20:08,546 --> 00:20:10,455
Thee art thinking of shipping.
你们想要出海

234
00:20:10,715 --> 00:20:13,003
I art.... I mean, I doest.
我是，我是说，我不是……

235
00:20:13,092 --> 00:20:17,421
-Making sport of me, lad?  你在逗我玩吗，小伙子？
-No. I just fell into that manner of speech.  不，我只是不太会语法

236
00:20:17,596 --> 00:20:19,553
If I weren't a Quaker and a man of peace...
如果我不是贵格会(属于基督教派，废除礼仪，反对暴力和战争)的教徒，而且爱好和平的话……

237
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:23,637
I'd fetch thee clout on the side of thy head,
my lad, just to make sure.
我要打你一个耳光，我的孩子，只是为了确定一下。

238
00:20:24,603 --> 00:20:26,928
I see thee art no New Bedford man.
我看你们不是新贝德福德本地人啊

239
00:20:27,105 --> 00:20:29,678
Doest know nothing at all about whaling,
I daresay.
我敢说你们对捕鲸一窍不通吧

240
00:20:29,774 --> 00:20:31,932
I've had several voyages
in the merchant service.
我以前跟着商船出过几次海

241
00:20:32,026 --> 00:20:34,065
Merchant service? Flukes, man.
商船？那只是侥幸，真的

242
00:20:34,361 --> 00:20:38,110
-What takes thee whaling? 你们为什么要捕鲸？
-Sir, I want to see what whaling is like. 长官，我想看看鲸鱼是什么样

243
00:20:38,282 --> 00:20:40,737
Have you seen Ahab,
the captain of this ship?
你们见过这艘船的船长亚哈了吗？

244
00:20:40,826 --> 00:20:42,485
If you want to know what whaling is...
如果你们想知道捕鲸是怎么回事……

245
00:20:42,577 --> 00:20:45,447
the n you'll know by clapping an eye
on Captain Ahab.
你们先看一眼亚哈船长就知道了

246
00:20:46,122 --> 00:20:49,158
You'll see a man torn apart
from crown to heel...
你们可以看到一个被从头到脚撕碎

247
00:20:49,292 --> 00:20:53,040
and spliced together with
sperm whalebone in place of what's missing.
然后再用抹香鲸的须子缝合起来的人

248
00:20:53,629 --> 00:20:57,958
His looks tell more than any church-had
sermon about the mortality of man.
他的外表比任何教堂里关于人类死亡的说教都更能说明问题

249
00:20:58,592 --> 00:21:00,150
And a whale did that?
这是一只鲸鱼干的？

250
00:21:00,818 --> 00:21:03,106
A whale as big as an island.
一头像岛一样大的鲸鱼

251
00:21:04,822 --> 00:21:08,404
Art thee the man to pitch a harpoon
down a whale's throat and jump after it?
你是那种能把鱼叉扎进鲸鱼的喉咙然后再跳上去的人吗？

252
00:21:08,492 --> 00:21:10,034
I am, sir...
是的，长官……

253
00:21:10,118 --> 00:21:13,700
if it should be positively indispensable
to do so.
如果这样做是必要的话

254
00:21:13,830 --> 00:21:15,490
Come along, then.
那就过来吧

255
00:21:19,460 --> 00:21:22,875
Bildad, stir yourself.
This young man says he wants to ship.
比勒达，打起精神来。 这个年轻人说他想出海

256
00:21:22,963 --> 00:21:25,798
-Hast ever been a pirate, hast thee?  你没当过海盗吧？
-Never.从来有

257
00:21:26,133 --> 00:21:30,082
-Didst not murder thy last captain at sea?  上次出海没有把船长杀掉吧？
-lndeed not. 真没有

258
00:21:30,845 --> 00:21:32,090
He'll do.
他没问题了

259
00:21:32,180 --> 00:21:35,679
-What pay shall we give him? 我们怎么给他开工资？
-The 777th part. 777先令

260
00:21:35,766 --> 00:21:39,099
-Would not be too much? 这不会太多了吗？
-For this strapping lad? Not half enough.  这么魁梧的小伙子？ 一点都不多

261
00:21:39,186 --> 00:21:41,428
Captain Peleg, thee hast a generous heart.
法勒船长，你有一颗慷慨的心。

262
00:21:41,521 --> 00:21:45,270
But thee must consider the duty thee owest
to the other owners of this ship...
但是你必须考虑你对这艘船的其他船主所负的责任

263
00:21:45,358 --> 00:21:47,066
widows and orphans, many of them.
他们很多是寡妇和孤儿，

264
00:21:47,152 --> 00:21:50,152
If we too abundantly reward
the labors of this young man...
如果我们给这个年轻人过高的薪酬……

265
00:21:50,238 --> 00:21:51,946
we'll be taking bread from their mouths.
我们会让他们吃不上饭的

266
00:21:52,031 --> 00:21:54,985
I'm putting him down
for the 300th part of the profit.
从利润里出300先令给他

267
00:21:55,075 --> 00:21:57,282
You hear, Bildad? The 300th part, I say.
你听见了，比勒达？ 我说300先令

268
00:21:57,369 --> 00:21:59,611
"Lay not up for yourself
treasures upon earth...
“不要把自己的财报财富堆积在地上

269
00:21:59,705 --> 00:22:01,662
"where moth and rust do corrupt."
蛀虫和铁锈会侵蚀它们……”

270
00:22:01,748 --> 00:22:05,792
-My last pay was--   我上一次的工资是
-The 777th part seems fair enough to me.  我觉得777 先令挺公道的

271
00:22:05,877 --> 00:22:09,708
-The 300th.就 300先令
-Don't thank me, lad. I only do thee justice. 别谢我，我只是秉公办事

272
00:22:15,302 --> 00:22:17,129
What holds thee? Sign.
你还犹豫什么？ 签字

273
00:22:18,221 --> 00:22:21,257
-Sir, it's Captain Ahab.  长官，关于亚哈船长
-What about him?  他怎么了？

274
00:22:22,058 --> 00:22:24,763
Was not Ahab of old a very wicked king?
亚哈不是古代一个很邪恶的暴君吗？

275
00:22:25,144 --> 00:22:27,813
And when he was slain,
did the dogs not lick his blood?
当他被杀的时候，连狗都不会舔他的血？

276
00:22:27,897 --> 00:22:30,304
Look, lad,
Captain Ahab did not name himself.
听着，小伙子，亚哈船长的名字也不是他自己起的

277
00:22:30,399 --> 00:22:34,693
Sign the paper now, and wrong him not
because he happens to have a wicked name.
现在就把这文件签了，不要因为他碰巧有一个邪恶的名字而误会他

278
00:22:39,632 --> 00:22:42,419
Now for that son of darkness
that is thy friend.
现在是为你那个深色皮肤的朋友

279
00:22:42,509 --> 00:22:44,418
Queequeg, step forward.
魁魁格，站出来

280
00:22:46,596 --> 00:22:48,340
What say you, Bildad?
你说呢，比勒达？

281
00:22:48,598 --> 00:22:51,089
I suspect thee art not a Christian.
我怀疑你不是个基督徒

282
00:22:51,392 --> 00:22:53,848
Doest thee attend church on Sundays?
你礼拜天去教堂吗？

283
00:22:54,103 --> 00:22:57,057
Doest thee know and obey
the Ten Commandments?
你们知道遵从十诫吗？

284
00:23:09,367 --> 00:23:10,778
God, man.
上帝啊

285
00:23:10,868 --> 00:23:15,197
Take the pen. Make thy mark.
Sign now for a 60th part of our profit.
拿笔，先做个记号, 签好了就可以领六十先令

286
00:23:15,456 --> 00:23:16,998
Put there, quick.
这里，快点

287
00:23:37,226 --> 00:23:38,969
Lantern kegs: 15.
灯笼桶： 15

288
00:23:39,728 --> 00:23:41,637
Rubber pipes: 10.
橡皮管：10

289
00:23:59,496 --> 00:24:00,990
Avast, there!
停!

290
00:24:01,873 --> 00:24:04,079
Are you going aboard, shipmate?
你要去国外吗，船友？

291
00:24:04,167 --> 00:24:06,788
Have you signed to sail on that ship?
你已经签约这艘船了？

292
00:24:06,877 --> 00:24:09,036
Have you signed to sail the Pequod, I say?
我说，你们已经签约斐廓德号了吗？

293
00:24:09,129 --> 00:24:11,799
Was there anything down
about signing away your souls?
你们对于出卖自己的灵魂有什么问题吗？

294
00:24:11,882 --> 00:24:14,170
-What? 什么？
-Perhaps you haven't got any. 可能你根本就没有灵魂

295
00:24:14,259 --> 00:24:17,710
-Have you met old Ahab yet?  你见过老亚哈了吗？
-What are you jabbering about? 你在支支吾吾些什么？

296
00:24:17,804 --> 00:24:21,604
Did they say how his mother birthed him,
gave him his evil name, and died?
他们告没告诉你他的妈妈如何生下他，起了这个邪恶的名字，然后死去的？

297
00:24:21,698 --> 00:24:24,106
How God's lightning struck down
and branded him?
上帝的闪电是如何击中他, 留下烙印的？

298
00:24:24,201 --> 00:24:27,201
How he spat in the holy goblet
in church of Valparaiso?
他是如何在 瓦尔帕莱索（智利中部城市）的教堂里朝圣杯里吐痰的？

299
00:24:27,287 --> 00:24:29,410
Did they tell you about his last voyage?
他们和你讲他上一次航行了吗？

300
00:24:29,497 --> 00:24:32,284
I know all about him being crippled
by a whale. Come on.
我对他被一条鲸鱼弄残了腿这事很清楚。走吧

301
00:24:32,375 --> 00:24:35,459
All about it? You're sure you do? Sure?
整件事情？你确认你很清楚，真的吗？

302
00:24:35,544 --> 00:24:38,117
Did they say how the whale marked him
inside and out...
他们有没有说鲸鱼是如何把他从头到脚都做了标记……

303
00:24:38,213 --> 00:24:41,463
and a mischief was worked on his soul?
No, I don't think they did.
而且让他的精神出了问题？ 
不，他们没说

304
00:24:41,550 --> 00:24:44,301
-Who'd know? Not many, I guess. 谁知道呢？我想没几个人
-You can't fool us.  你骗不了我们

305
00:24:44,386 --> 00:24:47,303
It's very easy for a man to look like
he's got a great secret.
一个人想要装作自己知道个大秘密是很容易的

306
00:24:47,388 --> 00:24:48,882
I have, lad.
我真的知道，小伙子

307
00:24:49,307 --> 00:24:53,221
At sea one day,
you'll smell land where there be no land.
在海上，总有一天你会在没有陆地的地方闻到陆地的气味

308
00:24:53,561 --> 00:24:58,021
On that day, Ahab will go to his grave,
but he'll rise again within the hour.
到那日，亚哈必死，但很快会再次起身

309
00:24:58,190 --> 00:25:00,063
He will rise and beckon.
他会起身然后招手

310
00:25:00,150 --> 00:25:03,850
Then all, all save one, shall follow.
然后所有的人，除了一个之外，都将追随他的命运

311
00:25:05,905 --> 00:25:08,526
Morning, shipmates. Morning.
早上好，船友们，早上好

312
00:25:10,159 --> 00:25:12,033
May the heavens bless you.
愿上天保佑你们

313
00:25:14,079 --> 00:25:15,408
Hey, you.
嘿，我说

314
00:25:16,373 --> 00:25:18,615
-What's your name?  你叫什么名字？
-Elijah. 以利亚

315
00:25:20,251 --> 00:25:21,911
My name is Elijah.
我叫以利亚

316
00:25:34,264 --> 00:25:36,589
-Bible? 要圣经吗？
-No, thank you, Aunt Charity, I have mine. 不用了，谢谢嬷嬷，我自己有

317
00:25:36,683 --> 00:25:37,714
Bible?
要圣经吗？

318
00:25:37,809 --> 00:25:39,848
-Thank you, ma'am.  谢谢女士
-God bless you. 愿上帝保佑你

319
00:25:52,614 --> 00:25:57,192
Don't whale it too much on the Lord's day.
But don't lose a fair chance, either.
在礼拜日上不要捕太多鲸鱼，但也不要错过一次公平的机会

320
00:26:00,888 --> 00:26:04,802
Spring, you sons of bachelors!
Jump, spring, there, green pants!
快爬，你们这些小杂毛！跳上去，快爬，穿绿裤子的！

321
00:26:05,642 --> 00:26:07,385
You, Scotchcap!
你，带无边帽的！

322
00:26:07,477 --> 00:26:09,268
-Yes?  怎么了？
-Spring! 动起来！

323
00:26:09,354 --> 00:26:12,687
Good white cedar plank is 3% more this year
than the last.
今年优质白雪松木板比去年贵了3%

324
00:26:38,463 --> 00:26:40,420
Hoist the yards!
升起帆桁！

325
00:26:40,507 --> 00:26:44,089
Our boots and clothes are all in pawn
我们典当了衣服和鞋子

326
00:26:44,177 --> 00:26:49,052
Go down, you blood red roses, go down
下去吧，你这鲜红的玫瑰，下去吧

327
00:26:49,348 --> 00:26:52,883
And it's mighty drafty
round the Cape of Storms
在风暴之角，周围风很大

328
00:26:52,976 --> 00:26:57,437
Go down, you blood red roses, go down
下去吧，你这鲜红的玫瑰，下去吧

329
00:26:57,522 --> 00:27:00,060
Oh, you pinks and posies
哦，你们这些粉红色的

330
00:27:00,150 --> 00:27:04,610
Go down, you blood red roses, go down
下去吧，你这鲜红的玫瑰，下去吧


331
00:27:04,820 --> 00:27:07,228
Take care of the butter.
20 cents a pound, it is.
看好黄油，20美分一磅呢！

332
00:27:07,323 --> 00:27:09,066
Bildad, stop palavering away.
比勒达 ，别废话了

333
00:27:09,158 --> 00:27:11,530
Three years is a long while going.
三年是很长的时间

334
00:27:11,743 --> 00:27:13,652
God have you in his holy keeping.
上帝会照看好你们的

335
00:27:13,745 --> 00:27:16,117
For that is where them whalefish blow
因为那是他们捕鲸的地方

336
00:27:16,206 --> 00:27:19,159
Go down, you blood red roses
下去吧，你这鲜红的玫瑰，下去吧

337
00:27:19,250 --> 00:27:21,622
Avast! Heave it!
停！举起来！

338
00:27:22,253 --> 00:27:23,830
Heave it there!
扔到那边！

339
00:27:26,215 --> 00:27:27,625
Heave away, forward.
起锚，前进

340
00:27:27,716 --> 00:27:31,714
There 's some that's bound
for New York town
有一些是开往纽约的

341
00:27:31,803 --> 00:27:34,757
And others is bound for France
还有一些开往法国

342
00:27:34,848 --> 00:27:38,679
Heave away, my Johnny
起锚了，我的孩子

343
00:27:39,063 --> 00:27:42,030
Heave away
起锚了

344
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:45,987
And some that's bound for the Bengal Bay
还有些开往孟加拉湾

345
00:27:46,082 --> 00:27:48,324
To teach them whales to dance
教那里的鲸鱼跳舞

346
00:27:48,418 --> 00:27:51,537
And away, my Johnny boy
起锚了，我的孩子

347
00:27:51,629 --> 00:27:54,914
We're all bound to go
我们都要出发了

348
00:27:55,007 --> 00:27:58,422
Come all you hard-weathered sailors
来吧，你们这些从风暴角来的

349
00:27:58,510 --> 00:28:01,261
Who round the Cape of Storms
饱经风霜的水手

350
00:28:01,346 --> 00:28:05,094
Heave away, my Johnny
起锚了，我的孩子

351
00:28:05,391 --> 00:28:08,511
Heave away
起锚了

352
00:28:08,603 --> 00:28:11,936
Be sure your boots and oilskins on
一定要穿好靴子和雨衣

353
00:28:12,022 --> 00:28:14,430
Or you'll wish you'd never been born
不然你们会后悔的

354
00:28:14,566 --> 00:28:17,567
And away, my Johnny boy
起锚了，我的孩子

355
00:28:17,652 --> 00:28:21,103
We 're all bound to go
我们都要出发了

356
00:28:44,802 --> 00:28:47,090
Set the topsails!
定好后帆！

357
00:29:18,249 --> 00:29:20,423
Up helm.
使船向风

358
00:29:25,688 --> 00:29:28,523
And around the world!
驶向世界！

359
00:29:44,539 --> 00:29:48,868
The Pequod beat an easterly course
toward the whaling grounds off the Azores.
"裴廓德号"向东驶去
去亚速尔群岛附近的捕鲸场

360
00:29:49,418 --> 00:29:53,795
The crew came from all the isles of the sea,
all the ends of the earth:
船员们来自五湖四海，全球各地：

361
00:29:53,880 --> 00:29:55,789
from Greenland to Mombasa...
从格陵兰（世界上最大的岛屿)到蒙巴萨(肯尼亚第二大城市）…

362
00:29:55,882 --> 00:29:58,420
from Clyde to Kokovoko.
从克莱德（位于西南苏格兰）到Kokovoko（魁魁格的家乡，实际不存在）

363
00:29:58,885 --> 00:30:02,799
Flask, the third mate,
bullied everybody bigger than himself...
大副弗拉斯克，欺负每一个块头比较自己大的人…

364
00:30:02,889 --> 00:30:06,803
particularly whales,
with whom he carried on a one-sided feud...
尤其对鲸鱼他有一种单方面的积怨……

365
00:30:06,892 --> 00:30:10,972
as though the great leviathans
had mortally insulted him and his forebears.
就像大海兽对他和他的祖先进行了致命的侮辱一样。

366
00:30:11,396 --> 00:30:15,441
And there was Pip, black little Pip,
the cabin boy from Alabama.
那是匹普，黑皮肤的小匹普，
来自阿拉巴马州的客舱服务员。

367
00:30:15,900 --> 00:30:18,142
Second in command was Starbuck...
副船长是斯达巴克

368
00:30:18,236 --> 00:30:22,019
whose Quaker stock had furnished
many a whaleboat with its champion.
他的贵格会血统，把很多拥护者带上了捕鲸小艇

369
00:30:22,114 --> 00:30:24,190
No crusader after perils...
和那些追逐危险的十字军战士不同

370
00:30:24,283 --> 00:30:28,991
his courage was one of the great staples
of the ship, like beef or flour:
他的勇气在需要的时候，是这艘船主要的支柱之一,

371
00:30:29,121 --> 00:30:32,572
there when required,
and not to be foolishly wasted.
 就如同牛肉或面粉一样: 不能被轻易浪费

372
00:30:33,249 --> 00:30:34,578
Ship 's carpenter:
船上的木匠：

373
00:30:34,667 --> 00:30:38,416
he fixed everything
from stove boats to broken arms and legs.
他修理从破船到断臂在内的一切

374
00:30:39,422 --> 00:30:44,083
Perth, the blacksmith, lived amidst
thick, hovering flights of sparks.
铁匠柏斯,终日生活在盘旋在空中的浓密火星之中

375
00:30:44,468 --> 00:30:47,801
He breathed them in and out.
They nested in his ears.
他把它们吸入又呼出，耳朵里也积攒了不少

376
00:30:48,096 --> 00:30:51,132
But Perth cared not because, as he said...
不过柏斯不在乎，他说：

377
00:30:51,224 --> 00:30:55,056
he was scorched all over,
and you cannot scorch a scar.
他浑身都被烫了一个遍，而疤痕是不怕烫的

378
00:30:56,145 --> 00:30:58,268
Queequeg was our first harpooneer.
魁魁格是我们第一个鱼叉手

379
00:30:58,481 --> 00:31:02,541
Next was Tashtego, the Indian
from a great warrior race of red men...
下一个是塔斯蒂哥，美洲印第安人，来自一个著名战斗种族…

380
00:31:02,625 --> 00:31:04,950
come to hunt whale instead of buffalo.
放弃了野牛而来捕鲸

381
00:31:05,420 --> 00:31:09,464
Then Daggoo, who got his boldness
and majesty and grace...
然后是达古，他独自杀死了一只狮子并把肉分给族人

382
00:31:09,632 --> 00:31:13,676
from having killed a lion single-handed
and partaken of its flesh.
他因此赢得了勇气，威严和荣耀

383
00:31:14,303 --> 00:31:16,010
Stubb, the second mate.
斯塔布，二副。

384
00:31:16,096 --> 00:31:20,307
Stubb, who 'd have tied a bowline
in the devil's tail for a joke.
斯塔布，他为了好玩可以在魔鬼的尾巴上打个领结

385
00:31:20,975 --> 00:31:24,925
Carefree, foolish, laughing, wise Stubb.
无忧无虑，总在傻笑的聪明的斯塔布

386
00:31:26,939 --> 00:31:30,806
Of our supreme lord and dictator,
there was no sign.
至于我们的最高领袖和独裁者,没有任何动静。

387
00:31:31,485 --> 00:31:34,936
Ahab stayed silent
behind his locked door...
整个白天,亚哈总是待在他紧锁的门后

388
00:31:35,030 --> 00:31:36,903
all the daylight hours.
保持沉默……

389
00:32:31,372 --> 00:32:33,946
It's him again. It's Ahab.
又是他，是亚哈

390
00:32:34,459 --> 00:32:37,163
Ahab come out in moonlight.
亚哈在月亮升起时出来活动

391
00:32:38,254 --> 00:32:39,550
Strange.
奇怪

392
00:32:42,023 --> 00:32:43,517
Only at night.
只在晚上

393
00:32:44,567 --> 00:32:47,402
Every night, all alone, walking the deck.
每天晚上，独自一人，在甲板上踱步

394
00:33:01,416 --> 00:33:04,085
"Sand it, holystone it," they say.
"用砂纸打磨，再用磨石磨平” 他们说

395
00:33:04,919 --> 00:33:07,077
And when you're done, what happens?
做完之后呢，会怎么样？

396
00:33:07,171 --> 00:33:09,163
"Start over again," they say.
他们会说 ”再来一遍，“

397
00:33:09,840 --> 00:33:13,789
"Clean it up, sand it down, buff it off."
"擦干净，磨平，再擦亮"

398
00:33:14,678 --> 00:33:19,339
Keeps you busy, lad. No time for mischief.
Here we go.
总是忙个不停，没时间瞎折腾，我们开始干吧

399
00:33:37,115 --> 00:33:39,273
Looming straight up and over us...
亚哈船长站在那里

400
00:33:39,367 --> 00:33:43,198
Like a solid iron figurehead
suddenly thrust into our vision...
就像一个坚硬的铁头像突然闯入我们的视野……

401
00:33:43,454 --> 00:33:45,161
stood Captain Ahab.
在我们的上方赫然耸现

402
00:33:45,706 --> 00:33:48,196
His whole, high, broad form...
他那高大、宽阔的身躯……

403
00:33:48,291 --> 00:33:52,787
weighed down upon a barbaric white leg
carved from the jawbone of a whale.
都压在一条用鲸的颚骨雕刻而成的野蛮的白腿上

404
00:33:54,047 --> 00:33:57,296
He did not feel the wind
or smell the salt air.
他感觉不到海风或是闻一闻咸咸的空气。

405
00:33:58,008 --> 00:34:01,342
He only stood staring at the horizon...
他只是站在那里盯着地平线……

406
00:34:01,678 --> 00:34:06,387
with the marks of some inner crucifixion
and woe deep in his face.
带着内心苦难的痕迹,他脸上露出深深的悲哀。

407
00:34:10,478 --> 00:34:12,554
-Mr. Starbuck. 斯达巴克先生
-Sir?  船长？

408
00:34:12,980 --> 00:34:14,640
Call everybody aft.
把大家召集到船尾

409
00:34:16,650 --> 00:34:18,144
All hands aft!
全体到船尾集合！

410
00:34:20,837 --> 00:34:22,497
Down, mastheads!
桅顶上的，快下来！

411
00:34:33,223 --> 00:34:36,224
What do you do
when you see a whale, men?
看到鲸鱼的时候你会怎么做，伙计们？

412
00:34:42,523 --> 00:34:45,358
-Sing out for him! 唱起战歌！
-Aye! 对！

413
00:34:45,609 --> 00:34:49,357
-Good. What do you do next? 好，接下来呢？
-Lower away, and after him!  放下小艇，追上去！

414
00:34:49,571 --> 00:34:52,144
And what tune is it you pull to, men?
你们要唱什么歌，伙计们？

415
00:34:52,240 --> 00:34:54,612
A dead whale or a stove boat!
不是鲸鱼死就是小艇沉！(流传于太平洋陆军的民歌，stove这里是busted的意思）

416
00:34:55,785 --> 00:34:57,694
All you mastheaders...
桅顶上放哨的……

417
00:34:59,080 --> 00:35:00,704
now hear me.
现在听我说

418
00:35:02,583 --> 00:35:03,994
You're to look...
你们要找的是

419
00:35:04,710 --> 00:35:07,379
for a white whale.
一只白色的白鲸

420
00:35:08,380 --> 00:35:12,163
A whale as white and as big
as a mountain of snow.
一只像雪山一样巨大而洁白的鲸鱼

21
00:35:16,429 --> 00:35:19,098
You see this Spanish gold ounce?
看到这枚西班牙金币了吗?

422
00:35:23,852 --> 00:35:26,058
Carpenter, hand me your top maul.
木匠，把你的大锤递给我。

423
00:35:31,067 --> 00:35:33,392
Whosoever of ye...
无论谁

424
00:35:33,694 --> 00:35:36,730
finds me that white whale...
帮我找到那只白鲸

425
00:35:37,281 --> 00:35:41,148
ye shall have this Spanish gold ounce,
my boys.
就可以得到这枚西班牙金币

426
00:35:51,210 --> 00:35:53,879
It's a white whale, I say.
我说,那是一只白色的鲸鱼

427
00:35:57,424 --> 00:35:59,138
Skin your eyes for him.
擦亮眼睛好好找

428
00:35:59,228 --> 00:36:04,191
Captain, sir, could it be the one that fantails
a little curious before he go down?
船长先生, 那只鲸鱼下潜前会扬起奇特的尾鳍?

429
00:36:04,280 --> 00:36:08,407
Has he a curious spout,
all bushy and mighty quick and high, sir?
他会喷出奇特的水柱, 又快又高 , 汹涌有力?

430
00:36:08,492 --> 00:36:13,035
And irons in his hide, many irons,
all twist around?
他的后背上有很多铁器，全都被折弯了？

431
00:36:13,121 --> 00:36:15,078
Aye, like corkscrews.
是的,就像开瓶器上的螺丝一样

432
00:36:15,206 --> 00:36:18,124
He's struck full of harpoons, men.
他身上插满了鱼叉,伙计们

433
00:36:18,209 --> 00:36:21,874
And his spout is a big one,
like a whole shock of wheat.
他喷出的水柱很粗大,像整整一捆小麦一样

434
00:36:21,962 --> 00:36:25,461
And he fantails like a broken jib in a storm.
他的尾鳍在风暴中就像一节三角帆

435
00:36:26,466 --> 00:36:28,589
Death, men, you've seen him.
死神，伙计们，你们见过他

436
00:36:30,595 --> 00:36:32,386
It's Moby Dick.
就是莫比.迪克

437
00:36:32,639 --> 00:36:34,133
Captain Ahab...
亚哈船长……

438
00:36:34,349 --> 00:36:37,848
was it not Moby Dick took off thy leg?
不就是莫比.迪克让你丢了条腿吗？

439
00:36:44,316 --> 00:36:45,644
Aye.
是的

440
00:36:46,693 --> 00:36:48,436
It was Moby Dick...
正是莫比.迪克

441
00:36:48,820 --> 00:36:53,778
that tore my soul and body
until they bled into each other.
撕碎了我的灵魂和肉体再把他们混在一起

442
00:36:58,370 --> 00:37:01,205
I'll follow him around the Horn...
我会跟着他到好望角

443
00:37:01,331 --> 00:37:04,498
and around the Norway Maelstrom...
到挪威旋涡……

444
00:37:04,626 --> 00:37:07,829
and around perdition's flames...
到地狱的火焰中……

445
00:37:07,921 --> 00:37:09,997
before I give him up.
也不会放弃

446
00:37:12,842 --> 00:37:15,511
This is what you've shipped for, men.
伙计们，你们出海的目的

447
00:37:16,387 --> 00:37:20,716
To chase that white whale
on both sides of land...
就是要追捕这条白鲸

448
00:37:21,433 --> 00:37:23,840
and over all sides of earth...
走遍天涯海角

449
00:37:24,686 --> 00:37:28,730
until he spouts black blood
and rolls dead out.
直到他喷出黑色的血液，翻滚着死去

450
00:37:30,191 --> 00:37:31,685
What say ye?
你说什么

451
00:37:33,110 --> 00:37:35,518
I think you do look brave.
我觉得你们看着很勇敢

452
00:37:36,822 --> 00:37:40,337
-Will you splice hands on it? 你们能在这件事上联手吗？
-Aye! 是的！

453
00:37:40,424 --> 00:37:43,508
Steward,
go draw the great measure of grog.
管家,去拿一大罐格罗格酒(掺热水的朗姆烈酒)。

454
00:37:43,594 --> 00:37:48,006
Harpooneers, get your weapons.
Mates, your lances.
鱼叉手们，拿好武器。
朋友们, 你的长矛。

455
00:37:49,391 --> 00:37:52,427
Ye mariners, now ring me in...
水手们，现在围到我身边来

456
00:37:52,894 --> 00:37:57,556
that I may revive a noble custom
of my fisherman fathers.
这样我可以重现一种我渔民父辈们的高贵风俗

457
00:38:00,734 --> 00:38:03,521
The measure. Drink and pass.
这壶酒，喝一口然后传给下一位

458
00:38:04,571 --> 00:38:06,196
Round with it, round.
把酒传一圈，传起来

459
00:38:06,281 --> 00:38:08,854
Quick draughts, long swallows, men.
快速喝一口，吞下肚，伙计们

460
00:38:08,950 --> 00:38:11,108
It's hot as Satan's hoof.
像撒旦的蹄子一样灼热

461
00:38:11,453 --> 00:38:14,655
That way it went, this way it comes.
从那边过去，从这边过来

462
00:38:14,747 --> 00:38:17,831
It spiralizes in ye.
赐予汝等神圣的力量

463
00:38:18,209 --> 00:38:19,868
Here, hand it me.
来，给我

464
00:38:20,794 --> 00:38:22,834
Well done. Almost drained.
很好，几乎喝干了

465
00:38:23,839 --> 00:38:25,416
Advance, mates.
前进，朋友

466
00:38:33,973 --> 00:38:35,882
Cross your lances.
把你们的长矛交叉

467
00:38:45,317 --> 00:38:48,602
Now, let me touch the axis.
让我摸摸轴心的部分

468
00:38:53,157 --> 00:38:54,437
Do you feel it?
你能感觉到吗？

469
00:38:55,200 --> 00:38:58,118
That same lightning which struck me...
击中我的闪电

470
00:38:58,745 --> 00:39:01,580
I now strike to this iron.
现在击中了这个铁器

471
00:39:02,624 --> 00:39:05,031
Does it burn, men?
很烫吧，伙计们？

472
00:39:09,588 --> 00:39:13,004
Harpooneers, break your weapons.
鱼叉手们，拆开你们的武器

473
00:39:13,550 --> 00:39:15,294
Turn up the sockets.
把凹槽翻上来

474
00:39:22,074 --> 00:39:24,280
Drink here, harpooneers...
喝吧，鱼叉手们……

475
00:39:24,827 --> 00:39:27,234
drink and swear.
对酒发誓

476
00:39:28,121 --> 00:39:30,114
God hunt us all...
如果我们不能把莫比迪克捉住杀死

477
00:39:31,124 --> 00:39:35,536
if we do not hunt Moby Dick to his death.
上帝会把我们一网打尽

478
00:39:43,177 --> 00:39:46,676
Death to Moby Dick!
为了莫比迪克之死!

479
00:40:05,822 --> 00:40:07,102
Moby Dick.
莫比迪克

480
00:40:08,575 --> 00:40:10,781
Do they name certain whales, then?
他们给鲸鱼起名字吗？

481
00:40:10,868 --> 00:40:15,577
Aye. Special, people-murdering whales
with long histories.
是的，那些有悠久历史的特别的杀人鲸

482
00:40:15,998 --> 00:40:19,117
Whales that have killed 10 times 100 men.
那些杀了上千人的鲸鱼

483
00:40:19,751 --> 00:40:22,871
Whales like Timor Tim,
New Zealand Tom...
像是帝汶岛的蒂姆，新西兰的汤姆，

484
00:40:23,004 --> 00:40:25,542
or Morquan, King of the Japan Seas.
或者摩根，日本海的王者

485
00:40:26,174 --> 00:40:29,091
Whales have big names
to go with big doings.
干过大事的鲸鱼都会扬名立万

486
00:40:29,802 --> 00:40:32,293
The biggest of them all is Moby Dick.
其中名气最大的就是莫比迪克

487
00:40:32,721 --> 00:40:34,714
A white whale, Ahab said.
亚哈说是一头白鲸

488
00:40:35,140 --> 00:40:36,551
Can a whale be white?
鲸鱼有白色的吗？

489
00:40:36,642 --> 00:40:41,054
He's white,
whiter than all the snow that ever fell.
他是白色的，比你见过的所有雪都要白

490
00:40:41,438 --> 00:40:44,687
Like a great marble tombstone,
he is, afloat.
像是一座漂在海面的大理石的墓碑

491
00:40:45,024 --> 00:40:49,816
Wherever he swims,
white sky birds wheel above him.
凡是他游过的地方，白色的鸟在上空盘旋

492
00:40:49,945 --> 00:40:53,396
-Birds white as the angels.  像天使一样洁白的鸟
-Which oceans does he swim in, Manxman? 他在哪里出没，马恩岛人？

493
00:40:53,490 --> 00:40:57,488
All oceans. He's been spied
in different seas 1,000 mile apart...
所有的海域，在相距一千英里之外的不同地方

494
00:40:57,577 --> 00:41:01,009
-on the same day at the same hour. 在同一时间都见过他的踪迹
-Maybe it just ain't one whale...  也许他不是一头白鲸……

495
00:41:01,096 --> 00:41:04,263
but a whole breed. 而是一群
Maybe Moby Dick's 100 whales. 莫比迪克可能是一百只鲸鱼组成的鱼群

496
00:41:04,433 --> 00:41:08,762
Then they all have crooked jaws
and wrinkled brows...
他们都有歪斜的颚骨和皱褶的额头……

497
00:41:08,853 --> 00:41:11,937
and a dozen irons stuck
in their white humps.
白色的驼峰上插着十几把鱼叉

498
00:41:12,607 --> 00:41:17,434
Aye, many have lowered for Moby Dick
and struck him...
是的，很多人都下艇叉过莫比迪克

499
00:41:17,653 --> 00:41:19,776
only to know his vengeance.
却只是领教到他的报复

500
00:41:20,239 --> 00:41:22,361
Some have boasted they killed him...
有人吹嘘他们杀了他

501
00:41:22,449 --> 00:41:25,450
but always he comes gliding back...
可他总是轻松的回归……

502
00:41:25,827 --> 00:41:29,659
huge and white and secret-like.
巨大的白色的，谜一样的存在

503
00:41:30,290 --> 00:41:31,949
Immortal, he is, they say.
他们说，他是不死之身

504
00:41:32,041 --> 00:41:34,496
You ain't trying to scare us, Manxman?
你不是在吓唬我们吧，马恩岛人？

505
00:41:34,627 --> 00:41:36,500
I say what I say.
我说的就是这些

506
00:41:36,837 --> 00:41:38,461
There she blows!
发现鲸鱼！

507
00:41:39,131 --> 00:41:42,914
Sperm whale to starboard!
There she blows!
抹香鲸在右舷! 正在喷水！

508
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:45,338
There go flukes!
尾叶在那里！

509
00:41:45,470 --> 00:41:48,043
-Flukes gone down! 尾叶潜下去了！
-Larboard!  左舷！

510
00:41:50,808 --> 00:41:52,386
Stow all line tubs!
装载所有小艇（里面有捕鲸用的绳子）!

511
00:41:55,479 --> 00:41:57,222
Fill up the mainsail!
主帆加满！

512
00:41:57,606 --> 00:41:59,314
Bear away, boats!
上小艇，去抢头功吧！

513
00:42:02,402 --> 00:42:06,648
-Bet you a dollar we strike first!  赌一美元我们先抓到！
-Right, Stubb. A dollar you don't.  好的，斯塔布，你输了一美元

514
00:42:13,328 --> 00:42:14,988
That's it, boys.
就这样，孩子们

515
00:42:15,622 --> 00:42:17,116
Pull, my men.
划啊，我的伙计们

516
00:42:17,207 --> 00:42:19,365
Why in the name of gudgeons
and ginger cakes...
你们是都没吃饱吗

517
00:42:19,459 --> 00:42:22,032
can't ye pull and start your eyes out?
你们就不能睁大眼睛划船吗？

518
00:42:22,462 --> 00:42:25,415
Why don't you break your backbones, boys? 使出吃奶的劲儿来，孩子们？
Pull, then. 用力划

519
00:42:25,506 --> 00:42:28,626
Do pull, will you, please? So, so now.
用力划啊，使劲儿行吗? 像现在这样

520
00:42:35,390 --> 00:42:37,928
Pull, boys! Pull!
划啊，孩子们，划啊！

521
00:42:38,768 --> 00:42:40,575
Pull, blast you!
划啊，被你们气死了！

522
00:42:40,661 --> 00:42:42,534
Take the oars off!
把桨拿下来划!

523
00:42:49,544 --> 00:42:51,417
Pull, my good boys.
划啊，我的好孩子

524
00:42:53,005 --> 00:42:54,499
That's fine.
好的

525
00:42:56,175 --> 00:42:57,373
Pull.
划啊

526
00:43:03,265 --> 00:43:05,387
Pull, my good boys.
用力划，好孩子

527
00:43:05,475 --> 00:43:07,551
Long and strong, boys.
每下都用力划到底，孩子们

528
00:43:08,353 --> 00:43:11,852
Pull and burst all your livers and lungs!
肝和肺都炸裂也没关系，用力划！

529
00:43:12,481 --> 00:43:14,806
Stop snoring, you sleepers!
别打呼噜了，你们这些瞌睡虫！

530
00:43:14,900 --> 00:43:16,608
Pull, can't ye? Pull!
划啊，你们行不行啊，用力！

531
00:43:16,902 --> 00:43:18,444
Merrily, hearts!
高兴点，用点心！

532
00:43:21,448 --> 00:43:22,646
Fine.
好的

533
00:43:24,075 --> 00:43:25,403
That's fine.
很好

534
00:43:27,412 --> 00:43:29,867
Come on, men. Pull ahead.
来吧，伙计们，向前划

535
00:43:32,499 --> 00:43:33,958
Pull, can't ye?
用力划，行吗？

536
00:44:30,485 --> 00:44:32,524
Man overboard!
有人落水！

537
00:44:34,447 --> 00:44:35,822
Cut him loose.
切断绳子

538
00:45:39,797 --> 00:45:43,795
Queequeg, my fine friend,
does this sort of thing happen very often?
魁魁格，我的好朋友，这种事经常发生吗？

539
00:45:43,884 --> 00:45:45,260
True, true.
是的，是的

540
00:46:03,376 --> 00:46:05,250
Heave away, boys!
起锚，孩子们

541
00:46:31,235 --> 00:46:33,726
And so we stripped our first whale...
于是我们把捕到的第一只鲸鱼剥了皮

542
00:46:34,321 --> 00:46:37,487
and boiled the blubber down
to a fine, pure oil...
用鲸脂熬成的上好的鲸鱼油

543
00:46:37,574 --> 00:46:40,491
that would keep the lamps burning
in a thousand homes...
可以让上千个家庭点亮油灯

544
00:46:40,577 --> 00:46:43,114
the clocks ticking on their mantelpieces...
让他们壁炉上的时钟滴答作响……

545
00:46:43,287 --> 00:46:46,656
and perhaps anoint the head of a king.
可能还能抹上国王的头

546
00:46:48,626 --> 00:46:52,623
And when at last we cast
the whale 's bared bones into the sea...
当最后我们把鲸鱼的裸露的骨头投进大海时…

547
00:46:53,422 --> 00:46:56,043
we were in no way sad at its funeral.
我们在它的葬礼上毫不悲伤

548
00:47:31,665 --> 00:47:32,779
Captain.
船长

549
00:47:36,836 --> 00:47:39,251
-Starbuck?  斯达巴克？
-Aye, Captain. 是，船长

550
00:47:39,980 --> 00:47:42,268
It's late. You should turn in.
很晚了，你该上床睡觉了

551
00:47:45,276 --> 00:47:46,521
Sleep?
睡觉？

552
00:47:47,862 --> 00:47:49,736
That bed is a coffin...
那床就像一口棺材……

553
00:47:50,197 --> 00:47:52,439
and those are winding sheets.
那些就是裹尸布

554
00:47:53,867 --> 00:47:56,488
I do not sleep. I die.
我不睡觉，我会死的

555
00:47:58,872 --> 00:48:03,617
The prize furnished 85 barrels of oil, sir.
They're all capped and stored.
一共炼出来85桶油，长官
都盖上盖子并存储起来了

556
00:48:03,710 --> 00:48:06,165
-How is the wind? 风向怎么样?
-North, northeast and steady. 北风,东北风很稳定

557
00:48:06,254 --> 00:48:10,203
Make the most of it. I do not wish
to linger on this Cape Verde ground.
充分利用它,我不希望 徘徊在佛得角的土地上。

558
00:48:10,424 --> 00:48:13,627
We're bound for the Pacific,
Mr. Starbuck, straightaway.
我们要去太平洋 斯达巴克先生,一直向前

559
00:48:13,719 --> 00:48:16,922
You will plot a course
south by east to the line...
你会绘制出一条准确的南偏东的航线……

560
00:48:17,013 --> 00:48:19,718
and so southeast
to pick up the Guinea current.
精确的东南向，可以遇到几内亚洋流

561
00:48:20,099 --> 00:48:21,594
Aye, aye, sir.
是的,是的,长官

562
00:48:22,351 --> 00:48:23,929
Mr. Starbuck...
斯达巴克先生

563
00:48:25,187 --> 00:48:29,267
did you ever ponder the movements
of whales around the four oceans?
你有没有仔细琢磨过些四大洋附近鲸鱼的运动规律?

564
00:48:29,817 --> 00:48:34,277
I only know that they appear at
certain feeding grounds in certain seasons.
我只知道他们在特定的季节出现在特定的觅食地。

565
00:48:37,240 --> 00:48:38,651
Look here.
看这里

566
00:48:41,410 --> 00:48:44,826
Logbooks from the time
New Bedford men first went a-whaling...
新贝德福德人刚开始从事捕鲸时候的日志……

567
00:48:44,914 --> 00:48:46,989
helped me draw this chart.
帮我画出了这张海图

568
00:48:48,834 --> 00:48:53,412
It divides the oceans into areas of
five degrees of latitude by five of longitude.
它把海洋按纬度和纬度分成了 5x5的区域

569
00:48:55,340 --> 00:48:59,882
Here are the months of the years,
the ships that passed...
这里是年月,经过的船只

570
00:49:00,011 --> 00:49:03,711
how long they lingered,
the whales they saw:
他们逗留了多久，他们看到的鲸鱼:

571
00:49:03,931 --> 00:49:08,177
what size, what color,
how many, where heading.
什么尺寸，什么颜色，
数量多少，往哪里游

572
00:49:08,351 --> 00:49:11,934
-I never saw the like. 我从来没见过这样的
-This way, the humpbacks go... 座头鲸往这边

573
00:49:12,021 --> 00:49:14,773
the blue, the right...
蓝鲸,去右边

574
00:49:15,608 --> 00:49:17,232
the spermaceti.
鲸脑油

575
00:49:17,318 --> 00:49:19,492
Sea mile by sea mile.
一海里一海里的

576
00:49:19,586 --> 00:49:23,251
I know their hidden journeys
as I know the veins in my arm.
我知道他们的秘密航线, 就像我对手臂上静脉的了解一样。

577
00:49:23,798 --> 00:49:26,633
You mean to say that
their journeys can be foretold?
你的意思是说他们的轨迹可以预知吗?

578
00:49:26,717 --> 00:49:31,178
Aye, like the blood pumping in my veins
from heart to hand.
是啊，就像我静脉里的血液一样
从心脏到手掌。

579
00:49:31,722 --> 00:49:35,850
If this be so, we can follow along
with the herds, killing as we go...
如果是这样，我们可以跟着他们的鱼群，一边捕猎…

580
00:49:35,934 --> 00:49:37,891
and fill our hold in record time.
在创纪录的时间里完成我们的任务

581
00:49:37,978 --> 00:49:40,647
So we shall, Mr. Starbuck. So we shall...
我们可以, 斯达巴克先生, 我们可以

582
00:49:41,147 --> 00:49:44,350
once we've attended to
our bigger business.
一旦我们开始更大的生意。

583
00:49:49,196 --> 00:49:51,189
What is that business, Captain?
那是什么，船长?

584
00:49:51,823 --> 00:49:54,493
Him, Mr. Starbuck. Him.
他, 斯达巴克先生, 他

585
00:49:55,744 --> 00:49:59,990
What's true of the herds holds largely
for the great solitaries and hermits.
鲸鱼群的规律,很大程度上也适用于那些独居的隐士

586
00:50:00,707 --> 00:50:04,538
If these sources tell the truth,
and my calculations are not faulty...
如果这些信息是真的, 而我的计算没有出错的话…

587
00:50:05,628 --> 00:50:08,415
he now swims the waters off Good Hope...
他现在游出了好望角……

588
00:50:08,505 --> 00:50:11,174
and all the Indian Ocean lies before him.
整个印度洋都在他面前

589
00:50:11,967 --> 00:50:16,877
Next month, he cruises the Bengal Bay,
March, the Sulu Sea...
下个月，他将巡游孟加拉湾，
三月，苏禄海……

590
00:50:17,722 --> 00:50:21,340
running eastward
to the gateway of the Pacific.
向东游去,到太平洋的门户

591
00:50:22,935 --> 00:50:25,260
I shall be waiting for him...
我会在四月的新月

592
00:50:26,230 --> 00:50:27,475
here...
在这里

593
00:50:28,148 --> 00:50:30,555
at new moon in April.
等着他

594
00:50:38,878 --> 00:50:40,158
Mr. Starbuck.
斯达巴克先生

595
00:50:40,254 --> 00:50:43,753
-I must give the helmsman our course. 我必须给舵手指明方向
-Come about, sir. 回来，先生

596
00:50:48,595 --> 00:50:52,924
Why are you wearing that long face? 你为什么一副不乐意的样子?
Are you not game for Moby Dick? 你不想抓到莫比迪克吗?

597
00:50:54,433 --> 00:50:57,185
Captain Ahab,
I am game for any kind of death...
亚哈船长,
我愿意接受任何形式的死亡

598
00:50:57,269 --> 00:51:00,701
if it comes in the way
of the business we follow. That be known.
如果它阻碍到我们所从事的事业,这你应该知道

599
00:51:01,122 --> 00:51:04,455
But I came here to hunt whales,
not my commander's vengeance.
但我来这里是为了捕鲸,不是为我的指挥官复仇。

600
00:51:05,084 --> 00:51:07,871
How many barrels of sperm oil
will thy vengeance yield?
为你报仇又能生产出多少桶鲸油呢?

601
00:51:07,962 --> 00:51:10,203
What will it fetch
on the New Bedford market?
在新贝德福德市场上它能卖多少钱?

602
00:51:10,297 --> 00:51:12,420
Money is not the measurer, man.
钱不是衡量的标准，伙计。

603
00:51:13,341 --> 00:51:15,879
It will fetch me a great premium...
它会给我心里

604
00:51:16,636 --> 00:51:17,799
here.
带来很大的安慰

605
00:51:18,638 --> 00:51:22,967
To be enraged with a dumb brute
that acted out of blind instinct...
被一个基于本能盲目行事的哑巴畜生所激怒

606
00:51:23,517 --> 00:51:25,095
is blasphemous.
这是一种亵渎

607
00:51:26,186 --> 00:51:29,222
Speak not to me of blasphemy, man.
别跟我说什么“亵渎”，伙计。

608
00:51:29,314 --> 00:51:32,730
I'd strike the sun if it insulted me.
就算是太阳侮辱了我，我也会把它射下来

609
00:51:36,654 --> 00:51:38,445
Look ye, Starbuck...
看看你，斯达巴克

610
00:51:39,490 --> 00:51:43,701
all visible objects
are but as pasteboard masks.
所有看得见的物体都不过是纸板做的面具。

611
00:51:44,620 --> 00:51:47,027
Some inscrutable yet reasoning thing...
某种神秘而又理性的东西……

612
00:51:47,122 --> 00:51:49,992
puts forth the molding of their features.
构成了他们各自的特点

613
00:51:50,500 --> 00:51:52,742
The white whale tasks me.
白鲸是我的任务

614
00:51:54,420 --> 00:51:56,496
He heaps me.
他填满了我

615
00:51:57,590 --> 00:51:59,796
Yet he is but a mask.
然而他也只是个面具

616
00:52:00,551 --> 00:52:04,595
It is the thing behind the mask
I chiefly hate.
我主要是不喜欢面具后面的东西

617
00:52:05,013 --> 00:52:09,176
The malignant thing
that has plagued and frightened man...
这恶毒的家伙从有时间开始

618
00:52:09,267 --> 00:52:11,592
since time began.
就一直困扰和惊吓着人类

619
00:52:12,020 --> 00:52:16,064
The thing that mauls
and mutilates our race...
这东西撕咬并残害我们的种族…

620
00:52:16,440 --> 00:52:20,438
not killing us outright,
but letting us live on...
不是直接杀死我们,而是让我们活下去…

621
00:52:20,527 --> 00:52:24,311
with half a heart and half a lung.
只剩下一半的心肺

622
00:52:25,198 --> 00:52:27,072
God keep us, keep us all.
上帝保佑我们，保佑我们所有人。

623
00:52:31,537 --> 00:52:34,621
The crew stands with me, Mr. Starbuck.
全体船员站在我这边，斯达巴克先生。

624
00:52:35,583 --> 00:52:37,575
You heard them swear.
你听到他们宣誓了

625
00:52:40,812 --> 00:52:41,891
Now...
现在

626
00:52:43,564 --> 00:52:45,687
what say ye?
你还有什么要说吗？

627
00:52:47,860 --> 00:52:50,979
Surely the best lance
out of all New Bedford...
毫无疑问，新贝德福德最好的长矛

628
00:52:51,071 --> 00:52:55,483
will not hold back
from the greatest hunt of all?
也不会阻止最伟大的狩猎吧？

629
00:52:56,534 --> 00:52:59,737
I say calmly back to thee, sir,
I am against thee.
我平静地回答你，长官，
我反对你。

630
00:53:00,746 --> 00:53:03,071
Nut thee needn't fear Starbuck.
但是你不必害怕斯达巴克

631
00:53:03,958 --> 00:53:06,448
Let Ahab beware Ahab.
让亚哈当心他自己

632
00:53:07,544 --> 00:53:10,117
Beware thyself, my captain.
小心点，我的船长。

633
00:53:24,434 --> 00:53:26,557
We left the winter seas behind...
我们已经把冬天的海洋抛在身后

634
00:53:26,645 --> 00:53:29,349
and sailed under the hot sun south.
在烈日下向南航行

635
00:53:29,773 --> 00:53:32,773
South, past the unseen sprawl of Africa...
向南，越过看不见的非洲大陆……

636
00:53:33,651 --> 00:53:38,478
until we rounded the Cape of Storms and
steered a bold course east and northeast...
直到我们绕过风暴角
大胆地向东和东北航行

637
00:53:38,572 --> 00:53:40,778
for the Indian Ocean and beyond.
去到印度洋更远的地方。

638
00:53:45,453 --> 00:53:48,240
-You there, lad, go aloft. 你，小伙子，到上面去
-Aye, aye, sir. 是的，长官

639
00:54:43,313 --> 00:54:46,848
And so I served my first watch
in the masthead...
于是，在一种优美流畅的节奏之中

640
00:54:47,317 --> 00:54:49,986
held in a great, gliding rhythm.
我第一次爬到桅顶上放哨……

641
00:54:50,236 --> 00:54:53,023
No life in me except that life imparted...
我的体内仅有的生命力

642
00:54:53,114 --> 00:54:55,486
by a gently rolling ship...
远离所有陆地居民的照料

643
00:54:56,158 --> 00:55:00,108
remote from all the cares
of the people of the land.
都是那艘轻轻摇晃的船所给予的。

644
00:55:10,880 --> 00:55:13,881
There she blows!
鲸鱼喷水！

645
00:55:17,761 --> 00:55:19,469
Where away? How many?
在哪里？ 有几只？

646
00:55:19,555 --> 00:55:21,381
Starboard bow, Mr. Stubb!
右舷，斯塔布先生!

647
00:55:21,765 --> 00:55:26,177
-Two! No, four of them! 两只，不，是四只！
-What's that boy yelling?  那孩子在喊什么？

648
00:55:26,269 --> 00:55:28,594
Six, seven of them!
六只，七只！

649
00:55:29,147 --> 00:55:31,554
There's three dozen more of them!
有三四十只！

650
00:55:31,732 --> 00:55:35,066
Look, Mr. Stubb! 100!
看，斯塔布先生，100只！

651
00:55:35,152 --> 00:55:38,022
Come down from there!
The sun has baked your brains!
冷静点!
太阳把你的脑子烤焦了!

652
00:55:38,113 --> 00:55:40,236
In the name of God, Mr. Stubb!
看在上帝的份上，斯塔布先生!

653
00:55:40,323 --> 00:55:43,573
A hundred, two hundred whales!
一百，二百只鲸鱼!

654
00:55:55,671 --> 00:55:57,793
Blast me dead, Mr. Flask.
该死的，弗拉斯克先生。

655
00:55:58,298 --> 00:56:00,472
All hands, prepare to lower!
全体人员，准备放下小艇!

656
00:58:04,236 --> 00:58:06,524
Another 40 barrels, sir.
又是40桶鲸鱼油，长官

657
00:58:47,149 --> 00:58:50,186
Ahoy, there!
Captain Boomer knocking at your door.
喂, 有人吗
布玛船长在敲你的门。

658
00:58:50,277 --> 00:58:52,815
-May he come in, sir? 他能进来吗，长官？
-Come aboard. 进来吧

659
00:58:59,953 --> 00:59:01,281
Captain Boomer's my name, sir.
我是布玛船长，长官。

660
00:59:01,371 --> 00:59:04,040
Ship's Samuel Enderby of London.
Eighteen months at sea.
在伦敦的塞缪尔·恩德比号轮船上服役，出海十八个月了。

661
00:59:04,123 --> 00:59:06,994
-Ahab. 亚哈
-Captain Ahab, will you look out there? 亚哈船长，你能看看那里吗？

662
00:59:07,084 --> 00:59:09,753
What a circus.
Did ever you see such a run?
真滑稽，你见过那样划船的吗?

663
00:59:09,837 --> 00:59:11,461
Do it, boys! Do it!
加油，孩子们，加油！

664
00:59:11,547 --> 00:59:14,666
Kill three for Captain Ahab
and three for me!
为亚哈船长杀三只
为我杀三只!

665
00:59:15,509 --> 00:59:17,750
Never fear. I'll not scuttle your ship.
不要害怕。我不会弄沉你的船。

666
00:59:17,844 --> 00:59:20,777
She's a beauty, eh, Captain?
Better than flesh and blood.
她很漂亮，对吗，上尉?
比血肉之躯更好

667
00:59:20,863 --> 00:59:23,484
Like her so much
I've a mind to have me other arm cut off.
我太喜欢她了，恨不得把另外一条胳膊也砍了

668
00:59:23,573 --> 00:59:25,862
The very thing for driving marlinspikes...
最适合用来钉马林钉（带尖的金属钉，用来固定成捆的绳子）

669
00:59:25,951 --> 00:59:28,192
knocking sense
into green seamen's heads...
可以让刚出海的水手脑袋开窍……

670
00:59:28,286 --> 00:59:31,370
and particularly good
for tapping kegs of rum...
而且敲朗姆酒桶也特别 好使……

671
00:59:31,873 --> 00:59:34,198
if you get my meaning, Captain.
如果你明白我的意思，船长。

672
00:59:35,042 --> 00:59:37,414
Pip, fetch rum.
皮普,上朗姆酒。

673
00:59:41,840 --> 00:59:44,461
I see you're wearing
a bit of ivory yourself, sir.
我看你也装了象牙的假肢，先生

674
00:59:44,551 --> 00:59:47,255
Lubbers with four limbs
don't know what they're missing.
四肢健全的人不知道他们错过了什么。

675
00:59:47,345 --> 00:59:50,796
When I got this ivory jib,
all spanking new and scientific...
当我装上这副象牙假肢，全新的科学产物……

676
00:59:50,890 --> 00:59:53,381
why, I could've thanked that whale.
我真该感谢那条鲸鱼。

677
00:59:54,768 --> 00:59:58,600
Aye, a whale took me arm for his breakfast.
Devilish big, he was.
是啊，一条鲸鱼把我的胳膊当作它的早餐。
他真是太巨大了。

678
00:59:58,689 --> 01:00:00,598
Pushed a tidal wave ahead with his nose...
用鼻子在身前掀起滔天巨浪……

679
01:00:00,690 --> 01:00:04,189
and typhoons jumped off his flukes
when they banged the water.
当他们哗啦哗啦地打水的时候，尾叶能掀起台风

680
01:00:04,360 --> 01:00:07,811
Old, he was,
and scarred like Jerusalem's hills.
他是老了,像耶路撒冷的山丘一样伤痕累累。

681
01:00:07,905 --> 01:00:11,356
Captain Boomer, what was his color?
布玛上尉，他是什么颜色的?

682
01:00:11,492 --> 01:00:15,192
He was white, sir. Think me crazy,
it's a fact. He was snowy white.
他是白色的，先生，你以为我疯了吧
可他确实是雪白的。

683
01:00:15,287 --> 01:00:17,161
Had another chance at him a month ago.
一个月前又有一次机会碰到他。

684
01:00:17,247 --> 01:00:19,405
You didn't kill him?
你没杀了他？

685
01:00:19,499 --> 01:00:23,746
Bless you, no. Went his merry way.
"Good riddance," said l, and meant it.
谢天谢地, 没有， 他哪儿来的回哪儿去了
“总算走了，” 我这么说的时候是认真的。

686
01:00:23,836 --> 01:00:26,374
Where did you last see the white whale?
你最后一次看到白鲸是在哪里?

687
01:00:26,589 --> 01:00:28,332
Off the Cape of Good Hope.
离开好望角的时候

688
01:00:28,424 --> 01:00:31,341
He was heading northeast
towards Madagascar.
他正朝东北方向的马达加斯加游去

689
01:00:39,017 --> 01:00:40,345
Do you hear?
你听见了吗？

690
01:00:41,394 --> 01:00:44,810
A white whale last month off Good Hope.
上个月一条白鲸离开了好望角。

691
01:00:44,897 --> 01:00:47,933
My chart is right and true!
我的海图是对的，没错!

692
01:00:48,275 --> 01:00:51,442
He'll be off Bikini
when the April moon is new.
在四月的新月，他会经过比基尼岛

693
01:00:52,279 --> 01:00:56,442
Stop the hunt!
Pick up our boats. We're setting sail.
停止捕猎!
收起我们的小艇。我们起航。

694
01:00:56,616 --> 01:00:58,858
But, Captain, those fine, big whales.
可是，船长，那么多上好的鲸鱼。

695
01:00:58,951 --> 01:01:00,960
You men up there, get aloft!
你们这些人上去，上去!

696
01:01:01,053 --> 01:01:04,753
I'll not sail with you, sir!
Bring my boat alongside.
我不和你一起航行，先生!
把我的小艇靠到边上来。

697
01:01:04,848 --> 01:01:07,469
Mr. Starbuck, cut loose that carcass.
斯达巴克先生，把那个鲸鱼尸体割下来。

698
01:01:07,559 --> 01:01:10,132
Pip, signal the men to return to ship.
皮普，给那些人发信号回船上来。

699
01:01:10,228 --> 01:01:13,228
What ails ye, sir? Are ye stove-in drunk?
你怎么啦，先生?你喝醉了吗?

700
01:01:13,314 --> 01:01:16,813
Captain Ahab, think what you're doing.
I beg thee, think.
亚哈船长，想想你在做什么。
我求求你，再考虑一下。

701
01:01:17,192 --> 01:01:19,813
-Set the mainsail! 升起主帆！
-No, sir, no! 不，先生，不要！

702
01:01:20,362 --> 01:01:22,520
Mr. Starbuck, are you opposing me?
斯达巴克先生，你是在反对我吗?

703
01:01:22,614 --> 01:01:26,445
If so, I'll have you know
there is one God that is lord over the earth...
如果是的话，我会让你知道
世上只有一位神，主管整个世界。

704
01:01:26,534 --> 01:01:28,989
and one captain over the Pequod.
斐廓德号也只有一位船长

705
01:01:29,704 --> 01:01:32,111
Away now! Cut loose!
现在离开，走了 ！

706
01:01:35,167 --> 01:01:37,622
Flask, what do you make of that?
弗拉斯克，你觉得那是什么意思？

707
01:01:38,211 --> 01:01:39,540
Return to ship.
让我们回船上去

708
01:01:39,629 --> 01:01:41,705
They're crazy, or I'm going blind.
他们疯了，不然就是我瞎了。

709
01:01:41,798 --> 01:01:44,086
You're not blind. Something's up.
你没瞎，肯定有情况

710
01:01:44,342 --> 01:01:47,378
Ye idiot, that's my whale
you're cutting loose!
白痴，那是我的鲸鱼
你让他跑了！

711
01:01:51,598 --> 01:01:54,054
Come aboard. We're setting sail.
回船上来。我们要起航了。

712
01:01:56,686 --> 01:02:00,850
Mr. Stubb, Mr. Flask, Did you not see
the pennant or hear my command?
斯塔布先生，弗拉斯克先生，你们没有看见信号旗或是听到我的命令吗?

713
01:02:00,940 --> 01:02:02,565
Yes, sir, we did.
长官，我们看到了

714
01:02:02,650 --> 01:02:04,109
Then why don't you obey?
那你们为什么不服从呢?

715
01:02:04,193 --> 01:02:07,941
We will, sir, as soon as it sinks in.
Sort of bowled us over, Captain.
我们一旦明白过来，就立刻服从了。
只是有点出乎意料，长官

716
01:02:08,030 --> 01:02:11,114
Weather's good, ship ain't sinking!
No one's lost overboard!
天气很好，船不会沉的!
没有一个人落水！

717
01:02:11,200 --> 01:02:14,366
Got a fine harvest here.
Don't see no reason to leave.
我们大获丰收，搞不懂为什么要离开

718
01:02:14,452 --> 01:02:17,204
I do not give reasons, Mr. Stubb.
I give orders.
我不做解释，斯塔布先生。
我只下命令。

719
01:02:17,288 --> 01:02:20,538
Now, Captain, we're good men.
Our blood's up, that's all.
听着，船长，我们是好人。
我们热血沸腾，就这样。

720
01:02:20,625 --> 01:02:21,787
We've been killing!
我们在宰鲸鱼！

721
01:02:21,876 --> 01:02:24,995
A hard thing to stop killing
when you've been killing steady, sir.
你杀得性起的时候很难停下来，长官

722
01:02:25,087 --> 01:02:27,756
We've been killing so fast,
our blood's so high...
我们杀得性起，热血沸腾……

723
01:02:27,840 --> 01:02:30,377
we wouldn't have heard the last trump.
没听到到最后的号角。

724
01:02:30,801 --> 01:02:32,710
Then hear me now:
那现在听我的：

725
01:02:32,969 --> 01:02:34,344
Come aboard.
上船

726
01:02:36,723 --> 01:02:39,739
All right, my hearties. Wake up!
Bestir yourselves.
好了，我的朋友们。醒醒吧!
犒劳一下自己

727
01:02:54,963 --> 01:02:57,798
This is an evil voyage, I tell you.
我告诉你，这是一次邪恶的航行

728
01:02:59,134 --> 01:03:01,173
If Ahab has his way...
如果按亚哈的命令行事……

729
01:03:01,428 --> 01:03:04,796
thee, nor me, nor any member
of this ship's company...
你也好，我也好，任何这艘船的成员…

730
01:03:04,889 --> 01:03:06,716
will ever see home again.
都再也回不了家了

731
01:03:06,808 --> 01:03:10,259
Come now, Mr. Starbuck.
You're just plain gloomy.
得了，斯达巴克先生。
你只是太悲观了。

732
01:03:10,728 --> 01:03:14,096
Moby Dick may be big,
but he ain't that big.
莫比迪克可能很大，
但他没那么大。

733
01:03:14,189 --> 01:03:16,229
I do not fear Moby Dick.
我不怕莫比迪克

734
01:03:17,359 --> 01:03:19,316
I fear the wrath of God.
我怕上帝发怒。

735
01:03:19,444 --> 01:03:21,021
The wrath of God?
上帝发怒？

736
01:03:22,113 --> 01:03:24,900
It is our task in life to kill whales...
我们这辈子的任务就是捕鲸

737
01:03:25,366 --> 01:03:28,485
and furnish up their oil
for the lamps of the world.
来为世界上的灯提供灯油

738
01:03:29,245 --> 01:03:32,198
If we perform that task well
and faithfully...
如果我们能忠实地完成好这项任务……

739
01:03:32,289 --> 01:03:35,705
we do a service to mankind
that pleases Almighty God.
我们为人类做出的服务，会令全能的上帝喜悦的。

740
01:03:35,792 --> 01:03:36,907
Aye.
是的

741
01:03:38,169 --> 01:03:40,245
Ahab would deny all that.
亚哈否认这一切

742
01:03:41,464 --> 01:03:44,334
He has taken us from the rich harvest
we were reaping...
他已经把我们从丰收的收割中带走

743
01:03:44,425 --> 01:03:46,880
to satisfy his lust for vengeance.
去满足他复仇的私欲

744
01:03:46,969 --> 01:03:49,542
He is twisting that which is holy...
他把本应神圣的使命

745
01:03:49,721 --> 01:03:52,592
into something dark and purposeless.
变得黑暗而没有意义

746
01:03:53,183 --> 01:03:55,389
He is a champion of darkness.
他是黑暗的拥护者

747
01:03:57,061 --> 01:04:00,679
Ahab's red flag challenges the heavens.
亚哈的红旗向上帝发出挑战

748
01:04:02,066 --> 01:04:06,015
Now, sir, if it's like that,
I don't wonder at you, a religious man...
现在，长官，如果是这样的话，
我能理解你，作为一个虔诚的人…

749
01:04:06,111 --> 01:04:07,819
being a mite downcast.
有点沮丧

750
01:04:07,905 --> 01:04:11,605
On the other hand,
don't much see what you can do about it.
另一方面，看不出你能做些什么。

751
01:04:12,659 --> 01:04:13,987
Listen to this.
听着

752
01:04:24,644 --> 01:04:26,969
"A captain who, from private motives...
“当一名船长出于私人动机……

753
01:04:27,063 --> 01:04:31,274
"employs his vessel to another purpose
than that intended by the owners...
“把他的船用于船东计划之外的其他目的…

754
01:04:31,734 --> 01:04:34,687
"is answerable to the charge
of usurpation...
是要被指控为“篡权”，并为此负责的

755
01:04:35,195 --> 01:04:37,768
"and his crew is morally
and legally entitled...
而他的船员们出于道义和法律

756
01:04:37,864 --> 01:04:41,565
"to employ forceful means
in wresting his command from him."
可以用强有力的手段从他手中夺取指挥权“

757
01:04:45,538 --> 01:04:48,373
That's a mouthful. I swear.
这真拗口，我说

758
01:04:49,124 --> 01:04:51,081
"Wrest his command from him "?
"夺去他的指挥权“？

759
01:04:51,168 --> 01:04:54,287
-Does that mean take over? 这是 接管的意思吗？
-lt does, Mr. Flask. 是的，弗拉斯克先生

760
01:04:56,006 --> 01:04:58,841
You ain't proposing we do any such thing?
你不会建议我们真这么干吧？

761
01:05:02,887 --> 01:05:07,548
You're in dangerous waters, Mr. Starbuck.
Helm hard over. Come about.
你正处在危险的水域，斯达巴克先生
强行夺权，改变航向

762
01:05:07,850 --> 01:05:09,558
Do thee not see...
你们看不出来……

763
01:05:09,893 --> 01:05:13,060
that by serving Ahab
we share in his blasphemy?
服从亚哈的话，我们就是和他一样亵渎上帝吗?

764
01:05:13,772 --> 01:05:15,681
Will thee risk that...
你们是宁愿冒这种风险

765
01:05:15,982 --> 01:05:18,555
or stand with me and invoke the law?
还是和我一起求助于法律吗？

766
01:05:19,402 --> 01:05:21,774
Pardon me, sir, this is my watch.
对不起，先生，到我站岗的时候了。

767
01:05:25,032 --> 01:05:29,243
Captains can't break the law.
They is the law, as far as I'm concerned.
船长不会犯法的。
就我而言，他们就是法律。

768
01:05:30,745 --> 01:05:33,497
Aye, and Ahab's a real fine captain, too.
是啊，而且亚哈也真是个好船长。

769
01:05:33,581 --> 01:05:36,155
Why, there ain't a man aboard,
except you maybe...
不然为什么，船上的人除了你

770
01:05:36,250 --> 01:05:40,711
wouldn't rather be kicked by him
than be knighted by the Queen of England.
都宁愿被他使唤，而不是被女王授勋

771
01:05:41,005 --> 01:05:42,547
I'm done, then.
那我没话说了

772
01:05:42,798 --> 01:05:44,837
Go write thy last will and testament.
去写你最后的遗嘱吧。

773
01:05:44,925 --> 01:05:47,594
Aye, and do it laughing, sir.
是啊，我会边笑边写的，长官。

774
01:05:53,725 --> 01:05:57,342
A laugh's the best answer
to all that's strange in life.
笑是对生活中所有的荒谬最好的回答

775
01:06:14,301 --> 01:06:16,210
As we steered out toward Bikini...
当我们驶向比基尼岛的时候……

776
01:06:16,303 --> 01:06:19,802
Ahab kept to his cabin
and was rarely seen.
亚哈一直待在他的船舱里，很少有人看见他。

777
01:06:20,265 --> 01:06:23,099
The mastheads were empty
against the sky.
桅顶在天空的衬托下空无一人

778
01:06:24,185 --> 01:06:27,304
No cry of "There she blows! "
was to entice us...
不再有人喊“鲸鱼喷水！"来让我们

779
01:06:27,438 --> 01:06:29,395
from his single purpose.
在他唯一的目的之外，得到一些额外的动力

780
01:06:30,274 --> 01:06:32,432
So, in April, with a new moon...
于是，在四月，伴随着新月……

781
01:06:32,693 --> 01:06:34,103
we entered those waters...
我们进入了

782
01:06:34,194 --> 01:06:37,479
where Ahab hoped to find the white whale.
亚哈希望找到白鲸的水域

783
01:06:47,414 --> 01:06:50,783
Lookouts, bestir yourselves!
哨兵们，打起精神来

784
01:06:51,668 --> 01:06:53,495
Lookouts up!
爬上岗哨！

785
01:06:56,673 --> 01:06:58,250
Look alive, lads!
注意，小伙子们！

786
01:06:58,341 --> 01:07:00,582
That gold belongs
to him with the sharpest eye.
金币是属于眼睛最尖的人的

787
01:07:00,676 --> 01:07:04,923
That coin's worth $16.
I'll be first to sight the white whale.
那枚硬币值16美元。
我将是第一个发现白鲸的人。

788
01:07:05,013 --> 01:07:09,675
Rum for me if I win the coin,
enough to dive into and never reach bottom.
如果我赢了这枚金币，给我买很多的朗姆酒
跳进酒桶的里，永远够不到底。

789
01:07:14,689 --> 01:07:16,100
Man overboard!
有人落水！

790
01:07:17,858 --> 01:07:19,353
Off the main yard.
从主甲板掉下去的

791
01:07:21,153 --> 01:07:22,944
Sea boat's crew away.
救生艇成员就位

792
01:08:03,624 --> 01:08:05,451
Not a sign of him.
没有他的踪迹

793
01:08:05,543 --> 01:08:08,413
Yeah. Sea just swallowed him up.
是的。大海把他吞没了。

794
01:08:10,464 --> 01:08:11,578
Queer.
奇怪

795
01:09:12,478 --> 01:09:14,850
April 19, 1842.
1842年4月19日

796
01:09:16,190 --> 01:09:20,120
Ahab's chart shows Moby Dick
and the new moon rising together.
亚哈的海图显示莫比迪克会和和新月一起出现

797
01:09:20,210 --> 01:09:22,416
Nut the moon's lost his horns...
但是直到月亏开始

798
01:09:22,670 --> 01:09:25,671
and there ain't no sign
of the white whale yet.
还是没有白鲸的踪迹

799
01:09:33,680 --> 01:09:36,171
Seven days and seven nights on watch.
值了七天七夜的班

800
01:09:36,891 --> 01:09:40,426
He ain't gone below, eats on deck,
sleeps standing up.
他不肯下去，在甲板上吃饭，站着睡觉。

801
01:09:41,229 --> 01:09:43,517
How much longer can he hold?
他还能撑多久？

802
01:10:17,762 --> 01:10:19,220
Nothing moves.
一点都不动

803
01:10:20,389 --> 01:10:21,669
Nothing.
一动不动

804
01:10:23,225 --> 01:10:25,716
Since the lookout fell into the sea...
自从岗哨落海之后

805
01:10:25,811 --> 01:10:28,728
the wind don't move, the tide don't move.
没有一点风，也没有一点浪

806
01:10:29,898 --> 01:10:31,226
Nothing.
一点都没有

807
01:10:32,567 --> 01:10:35,236
Even the sun's nailed to the sky...
连太阳都钉在了天空上

808
01:10:35,319 --> 01:10:38,486
Like that gold doubloon's
nailed to the mast.
就像钉在桅杆上的达布隆（古西班牙金币）。

809
01:10:45,578 --> 01:10:49,030
You, lad, pull that gold coin off the mast.
你，小伙子，把那枚金币从桅杆上拿下来。

810
01:10:49,123 --> 01:10:52,955
Throw it over the side.
Pay the sea a ransom.
把它扔到一边。向大海付一笔赎金。

811
01:10:53,085 --> 01:10:55,658
Maybe it'll come back to life
and bring us a wind.
也许它会恢复生机，给我们带来一丝风。

812
01:10:55,754 --> 01:10:57,414
Manxman, stop.
马恩岛人, 住手。

813
01:10:58,715 --> 01:11:00,225
A cool wind.
一阵凉风

814
01:11:02,443 --> 01:11:04,649
You, Manxman, stop!
你,马恩岛人, 住手!

815
01:11:20,751 --> 01:11:22,957
Queequeg, what are you doing?
魁魁格，你在做什么？

816
01:11:24,213 --> 01:11:27,463
See tomorrow here. Bones tell everything.
为明天占卜，骨头会告诉我一切。

817
01:11:39,393 --> 01:11:41,469
Queequeg, what's the matter?
魁魁格，怎么了？

818
01:11:42,855 --> 01:11:44,397
What do you see?
你看到什么了？

819
01:11:44,481 --> 01:11:46,059
Get carpenter.
叫木匠来

820
01:11:46,650 --> 01:11:48,975
What do you want the carpenter for?
你想叫木匠做什么？

821
01:11:52,572 --> 01:11:53,982
Carpenter.
木匠

822
01:11:56,033 --> 01:11:57,314
Here.
过来

823
01:12:03,999 --> 01:12:07,498
-What can I do for you?  要我做什么？
-How much you build coffin for? 你做一口棺材要多少钱？

824
01:12:08,128 --> 01:12:09,372
Coffin?
棺材？

825
01:12:11,297 --> 01:12:13,040
$2 would do nicely.
2美元可以做的很好了

826
01:12:13,632 --> 01:12:17,215
-Hold on.   等一下
-Build coffin. 6 feet, 7 inch. 做一口6英尺7英寸的棺材

827
01:12:17,886 --> 01:12:19,345
Clean wood.
干净的木头

828
01:12:19,555 --> 01:12:23,054
Make like best boat. Caulk and tar seams.
像做最好的船一样，接缝处用焦油做防渗水处理

829
01:12:23,308 --> 01:12:24,932
No water come in.
让水进不来

830
01:12:25,018 --> 01:12:27,687
Carve chief's feather on lid.
把酋长的羽毛刻在盖子上。

831
01:12:29,188 --> 01:12:32,771
-6 feet 7 inches, it'll be. 6英尺7英寸，好的
-Queequeg, what's all this about? 魁魁格，这些是为了什么？

832
01:12:32,858 --> 01:12:35,978
Money yours. Sea chest yours.
钱给你，储物箱给你

833
01:12:36,069 --> 01:12:38,311
My harpoon yours.
我的鱼叉给你

834
01:12:40,548 --> 01:12:41,828
Goodbye.
再见

835
01:12:48,096 --> 01:12:49,294
What?
什么？

836
01:12:50,140 --> 01:12:52,678
Queequeg, what are you talking about?
魁魁格，你在说什么啊？

837
01:12:56,646 --> 01:12:58,519
Queequeg, listen to me!
魁魁格，听我说！

838
01:12:59,148 --> 01:13:00,725
Say something.
说话啊

839
01:13:02,401 --> 01:13:06,066
-What are we going to do?  我们现在怎么办？
-There's only one thing to do:  只有一件事可做：

840
01:13:07,364 --> 01:13:09,155
build him his coffin.
帮他做棺材

841
01:13:48,443 --> 01:13:50,150
You've got to eat.
你得吃点东西

842
01:13:52,655 --> 01:13:54,398
A drink of water, then.
那就喝点水

843
01:13:58,243 --> 01:14:01,778
Queequeg, if you go on like this,
I shall be very angry.
魁魁格，你再这样我要生气了

844
01:14:04,541 --> 01:14:07,114
Queequeg, I absolutely forbid you to die.
魁魁格，我绝不让你死

845
01:14:16,259 --> 01:14:18,881
Such behavior simply isn't Christian.
这种行为是违反基督教义的

846
01:14:20,237 --> 01:14:23,606
In fact, it's downright pagan
and heathenish.
事实上，这完全是异教

847
01:14:28,662 --> 01:14:30,322
Remember our oath?
记得我们的誓言吗

848
01:14:30,580 --> 01:14:33,664
You promised to go where I go,
eat what I eat...
你答应过和我同吃同行

849
01:14:33,750 --> 01:14:35,409
ship on my ship.
同船出海

850
01:14:36,169 --> 01:14:38,790
I hold you to your promise, Queequeg.
我要你信守诺言，魁魁格

851
01:14:39,672 --> 01:14:41,629
I've seen this before, lad.
我以前见过这种情况，小伙子

852
01:14:44,176 --> 01:14:48,173
One day, for no reason,
they know that death is near.
有一天，他们无缘无故地知道死亡就在眼前。

853
01:14:49,055 --> 01:14:52,506
They give away all their belongings
and say goodbye.
他们把所有的东西都送人，然后说再见。

854
01:14:53,476 --> 01:14:55,468
Then they sit down to wait...
他们坐下来等待

855
01:14:56,520 --> 01:14:58,347
and they just die.
死亡的到来

856
01:14:59,189 --> 01:15:01,597
Mr. Starbuck, sir, Captain wants you.
斯达巴克先生，船长找你。

857
01:15:26,214 --> 01:15:27,376
Sir?
船长

858
01:15:30,551 --> 01:15:33,006
Mr. Starbuck, new orders.
斯达巴克先生，新的命令来了

859
01:15:36,765 --> 01:15:39,552
We remain here until eight bells tonight...
我们在这里一直呆到今晚八点…

860
01:15:41,686 --> 01:15:44,438
at which time we'll lower whaleboats...
那时我们就可以放下捕鲸小艇……

861
01:15:45,982 --> 01:15:48,223
kedge the ship north...
收拢锚链，让船往北移动……

862
01:15:49,902 --> 01:15:52,309
and row out of these waters.
从这片水域划出去。

863
01:15:53,280 --> 01:15:55,189
Aye, aye, sir. At eight bells.
是的，是的，长官。八点钟。

864
01:16:00,261 --> 01:16:03,629
I'm beating a march to you, Queequeg.
Get along.
魁魁格，我正在向你进军呢。跟上去

865
01:16:23,365 --> 01:16:25,238
Get along quiet now, Queequeg.
安静的走吧，魁魁格

866
01:16:25,325 --> 01:16:28,112
You follow the tide. It knows where to go.
你跟着海潮。它知道去哪里。

867
01:16:35,584 --> 01:16:39,035
You get along with it.
It'll take you, Queequeg. Get along.
你跟上它，他会带领你，魁魁格，跟上去

868
01:16:42,966 --> 01:16:44,543
Rig-a-dig.
忍一忍

869
01:16:45,969 --> 01:16:47,167
Rig-a-dig.
忍一忍

870
01:16:50,765 --> 01:16:52,389
He won't listen.
他不肯听

871
01:16:55,686 --> 01:16:58,603
Queequeg's going away.
Know where he's going?
魁魁格要走了。知道他要去哪里吗?

872
01:17:02,567 --> 01:17:04,606
Way, way up to Kokovoko.
一直到Kokovoko。

873
01:17:10,825 --> 01:17:13,611
Back to Kokovoko, where he came from.
回到kokovoko，他来自那里

874
01:18:42,715 --> 01:18:44,257
Queequeg, don't.
魁魁格，不要

875
01:18:45,801 --> 01:18:48,672
-There she blows! 鲸鱼喷水！
-Queequeg, listen to me. Don't. 魁魁格，听我说，不要

876
01:18:58,271 --> 01:19:00,513
Off the starboard beam!
在右舷横梁附近！

877
01:19:09,073 --> 01:19:10,317
It's him.
是他

878
01:19:11,325 --> 01:19:12,819
I know it's him.
我知道是他

879
01:19:17,121 --> 01:19:18,497
Is it real?
真的？

880
01:19:19,890 --> 01:19:21,384
Do you see it, too?
你也看见了？

881
01:19:21,475 --> 01:19:23,266
Aye, we all see it.
是的，我们都看见了 

882
01:19:23,935 --> 01:19:26,640
But that don't mean it's real, necessarily.
但这并不意味着它一定是真实的。

883
01:19:27,147 --> 01:19:29,139
Clear away the boats.
把小艇收拾干净。

884
01:19:29,273 --> 01:19:31,562
Lower for him now, sir? At night?
现在就放小艇追他吗，长官? 在晚上?

885
01:19:31,651 --> 01:19:33,026
Lower away.
放下小艇

886
01:19:34,153 --> 01:19:35,695
Away boat's crews.
全体船员准备

887
01:20:21,863 --> 01:20:23,143
He's sounded.
他听见了

888
01:20:26,158 --> 01:20:27,439
Ship oars.
收桨

889
01:21:26,896 --> 01:21:27,975
He's near.
他就在附近

890
01:21:29,523 --> 01:21:31,017
He's very near.
他 很近了

891
01:21:33,193 --> 01:21:34,901
Be ready for him.
准备迎击

892
01:21:48,332 --> 01:21:50,787
He breaches!
他冲出来了！

893
01:22:02,803 --> 01:22:04,298
The birds, they go.
海鸟飞走了

894
01:22:04,472 --> 01:22:06,464
God, I'll lose him.
上帝啊，他要甩掉我了

895
01:22:06,599 --> 01:22:09,136
Without a wind, we'll lose him!
没有风的话，我们跟不上他！

896
01:22:17,233 --> 01:22:20,150
That ain't no whale.
That a great white god.
那不是鲸鱼。
那是一个白色的神。

897
01:22:22,780 --> 01:22:25,152
About! Back to the ship!
可以了！回船上去！

898
01:22:25,532 --> 01:22:28,450
We'll tie on and row for a wind.
我们要系上绳子，划桨等到起风

899
01:22:33,206 --> 01:22:36,824
Long days and nights
we strained at the oars...
漫长的日日夜夜
我们使劲划桨……

900
01:22:37,668 --> 01:22:40,436
while the white whale swam freely on...
白鲸自由地游着……

901
01:22:40,937 --> 01:22:45,266
widening the waters between himself
and Ahab 's vengeance.
拉大着他与亚哈的仇恨之间的距离


902
01:22:54,283 --> 01:22:57,698
A cloud on the starboard beam.
右舷横梁方向有朵云

903
01:22:59,246 --> 01:23:02,614
Steer for the cloud, men. Bring her around.
驶向云朵，伙计们，转向

904
01:23:03,541 --> 01:23:06,114
For the cloud! Starboard!
驶向云朵，右舷！

905
01:23:14,926 --> 01:23:16,753
Pull quick!
快划！

906
01:23:16,928 --> 01:23:19,799
Pull us into it, boys. Quick.
我们要到云里面去，孩子们。快。

907
01:23:24,769 --> 01:23:26,049
Pull!
划啊！

908
01:23:27,479 --> 01:23:28,724
That's it!
就是这样！

909
01:24:00,426 --> 01:24:02,833
You raised the white whale first.
你第一个发现白鲸的

910
01:24:03,637 --> 01:24:05,594
The gold doubloon is yours.
金币是你的了

911
01:24:06,223 --> 01:24:08,215
Go on. Take it, sailor.
继续。拿走它,水手。

912
01:24:14,647 --> 01:24:16,853
Wait now. Listen.
现在等一下，听我是

913
01:24:17,775 --> 01:24:20,661
This man has his Spanish gold ounce.
这个人拿到了他的西班牙黄金盎司。

914
01:24:22,712 --> 01:24:24,586
You shall have yours.
当莫比迪克被击中并被杀死时……

915
01:24:25,673 --> 01:24:28,425
When Moby Dick is struck and killed...
你们也会有自己那一份的

916
01:24:28,509 --> 01:24:32,043
on that day, you shall have my share.
到那一天，我那一份也是你们的

917
01:24:32,638 --> 01:24:35,211
My 10% of the profits...
这次航行10%的利润

918
01:24:35,557 --> 01:24:37,799
of this entire voyage.
是属于我的

919
01:24:38,685 --> 01:24:39,799
Aye!
是的！

920
01:24:40,186 --> 01:24:43,970
Gold will pour out of Moby Dick's wounds
into your hands.
黄金会从莫比-迪克的伤口里流出来，流到你的手里。

921
01:24:44,565 --> 01:24:47,234
Every drop of his blood...
他的每一滴血

922
01:24:47,776 --> 01:24:49,935
another Spanish doubloon!
都是一枚达布隆金币！

923
01:24:50,446 --> 01:24:52,568
What say you to that, men?
你们觉得怎么样，伙计们？

924
01:24:54,241 --> 01:24:55,521
Sing out!
大声告诉我！

925
01:24:55,992 --> 01:24:59,740
They're all dumfounded, sir, and so am l.
他们都目瞪口呆，长官，我也是。

926
01:24:59,829 --> 01:25:01,738
Hooray for Captain Ahab!
亚哈船长万岁!

927
01:25:07,503 --> 01:25:09,294
Pip, grog all around.
匹普，给所有人倒酒。

928
01:25:09,379 --> 01:25:11,586
A sail, sir, to starboard.
长官，右舷发现一艘船

929
01:25:16,678 --> 01:25:18,421
The Rachel, out of New Bedford.
是瑞秋号，来自新贝德福德。

930
01:25:18,513 --> 01:25:21,003
Captain Gardiner's ship.
She's coming around.
嘉丁纳船长的船。她要过来了。

931
01:25:26,562 --> 01:25:30,429
Captain Ahab,
have you seen a whaleboat adrift?
亚哈船长,你看见过一艘漂流的捕鲸小艇吗?

932
01:25:30,523 --> 01:25:32,183
I've seen nothing.
我什么也没看见

933
01:25:32,817 --> 01:25:34,940
You've seen the white whale?
你见过那只白鲸吗?

934
01:25:35,028 --> 01:25:38,692
We harpooned him
not 10 miles from this spot.
我们刺中了他 离这里不到10英里。

935
01:25:38,906 --> 01:25:40,365
Not dead.
还没有死

936
01:25:40,950 --> 01:25:43,820
-You didn't kill him? 你没杀了他？
-No. 没有

937
01:25:43,911 --> 01:25:47,778
We lost a boat, towed out of sight by him.
To ruin.
我们有一艘小艇被他拖走了，不见行踪

938
01:25:47,873 --> 01:25:51,158
Three days and nights we've searched.
My boy was in it.
我们已经找了三天三夜了。
我儿子在里面。

939
01:25:51,251 --> 01:25:54,085
My own son. Twelve years old.
我的亲生儿子，12岁了

940
01:25:56,172 --> 01:25:58,923
Captain Ahab, will you help me search?
亚哈船长，你肯帮我找找吗?

941
01:25:59,008 --> 01:26:01,396
As we are Christians,
we cannot refuse this man.
既然我们是基督徒，我们不能拒绝这个人。

942
01:26:01,484 --> 01:26:04,057
You will. I know you will help!
你会的，我知道你会帮忙的！

943
01:26:04,821 --> 01:26:06,065
You must!
你一定得帮我！

944
01:26:06,155 --> 01:26:09,109
You must,
and you shall do this thing for me!
你一定要帮我，你应该帮我这个忙！

945
01:26:13,995 --> 01:26:16,486
If thee say no, we'll be in black disgrace.
如果你说不的话，我们就丢脸了。

946
01:26:16,581 --> 01:26:19,498
At home, they'll spit
at the mention of the Pequod's name.
回到家乡，他们都会唾弃"裴廓德号"的名字。

947
01:26:19,584 --> 01:26:22,075
Captain Ahab, answer me!
亚哈船长，回答我!

948
01:26:22,587 --> 01:26:24,330
Captain Gardiner...
嘉丁纳队长……

949
01:26:24,964 --> 01:26:27,537
I seek the white whale!
我要找白鲸!

950
01:26:27,925 --> 01:26:30,250
Your own son's murderer!
杀死你亲生儿子的凶手!

951
01:26:32,220 --> 01:26:34,426
I am losing time.
我没时间了。

952
01:26:34,723 --> 01:26:37,759
Time? I've lost my whole world!
时间吗?我失去了我的整个世界!

953
01:26:38,142 --> 01:26:41,926
I will not go.
I will follow till you say aye to me.
我不会离开。
我会一直跟着你，直到你答应为止。

954
01:26:42,813 --> 01:26:44,971
Run, men. Stand by to lower.
快去，伙计们，准备下船

955
01:26:45,816 --> 01:26:47,690
I am coming over, Captain.
我来了，船长。

956
01:26:47,776 --> 01:26:51,476
Avast! Touch not a rope! I must go.
停住! 别碰绳子! 我必须走了。

957
01:26:52,072 --> 01:26:55,321
Goodbye, I say, and fare thee well.
再见，我说，再见吧。

958
01:26:55,617 --> 01:26:58,617
God help you, Captain Gardiner!
愿上帝保佑你，嘉丁纳船长!

959
01:26:59,328 --> 01:27:03,076
God forgive you, Captain Ahab.
愿上帝饶恕你，亚哈船长。

960
01:27:15,760 --> 01:27:17,799
Stoke up the tryworks.
给炼油炉加满燃料

961
01:27:19,346 --> 01:27:22,051
We shall run forward laden with fire...
我们将要带着满载的火力前进……

962
01:27:22,766 --> 01:27:26,977
to render the white whale's flesh
into unholy oil.
把白鲸的肉炼成罪恶的油。

963
01:27:27,187 --> 01:27:28,645
Blacksmith...
铁匠

964
01:27:30,398 --> 01:27:32,805
I set ye a task.
我给你一个任务

965
01:27:39,201 --> 01:27:42,914
Take these harpoons and lances.
Melt them down.
把这些鱼叉和长矛拿去回炉

966
01:27:43,176 --> 01:27:44,718
Forge me new weapons...
给我打造些新的武器

967
01:27:44,802 --> 01:27:48,301
that will strike deep and hold fast.
要可以刺得很深，牢牢抓住。

968
01:27:48,597 --> 01:27:50,922
Nut do not douse them in water.
但是不要把他们沾到水

969
01:27:51,516 --> 01:27:54,186
They must have a proper baptism.
他们必须接受适当的洗礼。

970
01:27:55,186 --> 01:27:57,475
What say ye, all ye men?
伙计们，你们要说什么？

971
01:27:57,772 --> 01:28:02,481
Will you give as much blood
as shall be needed to temper the steel?
你们愿意付出足够多的鲜血来磨炼钢铁吗?

972
01:28:02,568 --> 01:28:04,027
Aye!
是的！

973
01:28:04,111 --> 01:28:06,732
To my anger, now add your own.
将你们的愤怒附加到我那一份之上

974
01:28:08,448 --> 01:28:11,319
You be the cogs that fit my wheel...
你们是我车轮上的齿轮……

975
01:28:12,535 --> 01:28:15,821
the gunpowder that takes my torch.
点燃我的火把的火药

976
01:28:17,540 --> 01:28:20,291
Pledge yourselves heart...
用你们的心

977
01:28:22,253 --> 01:28:23,711
soul...
你们的灵魂

978
01:28:25,297 --> 01:28:26,625
body...
你们的躯体

979
01:28:28,425 --> 01:28:30,832
-life and lung-- 你们的生命和呼吸来起誓
-Aye, sir. -- 是，长官

980
01:28:31,761 --> 01:28:34,548
...as I pledge myself.
和我一起发誓

981
01:28:37,266 --> 01:28:40,386
Death to Moby Dick.
杀死莫比迪克

982
01:28:41,478 --> 01:28:43,554
Death.
杀

983
01:29:20,196 --> 01:29:21,524
Up helm!
使船向风！

984
01:29:22,490 --> 01:29:24,613
Bring the wind aft!
把风吹到船尾!

985
01:29:40,381 --> 01:29:41,626
Hold it!
等等

986
01:29:45,344 --> 01:29:47,965
Sir, shall I shorten sail?
先生，我要收帆吗?

987
01:29:48,055 --> 01:29:50,545
No. She runs well enough.
不。船速很好

988
01:29:57,063 --> 01:29:59,139
Weather main brace!
打开主转桁索!

989
01:29:59,732 --> 01:30:01,890
Weather yards!
打开帆桁!

990
01:30:10,867 --> 01:30:14,567
The braces, men! Haul away!
转桁索，伙计们，拉开！

991
01:30:34,847 --> 01:30:38,216
Haul away! Lay on your backs and haul!
拉开！躺倒了往后拉！

992
01:30:38,517 --> 01:30:40,474
Earn your salt!
全靠你们自己了！

993
01:30:42,812 --> 01:30:44,935
By all that's holy, Captain!
天哪，船长!

994
01:30:45,023 --> 01:30:49,067
We'll lose every inch of canvas
if we don't ease the ship!
如果我们不让船减速，我们所有的帆布都会被刮跑的。

995
01:30:49,152 --> 01:30:50,527
Mr. Starbuck...
斯达巴克 先生

996
01:30:50,945 --> 01:30:53,696
we're three days behind Moby Dick!
我们比莫比迪克落后了3天的路程

997
01:30:54,031 --> 01:30:56,403
This wind is heaven-sent.
这风是天赐的。

998
01:30:56,867 --> 01:30:59,243
Heaven-sent to destroy us.
上天派来毁灭我们的。

999
01:31:04,223 --> 01:31:06,299
Cut away those rags!
把那些破布剪掉!

1000
01:31:06,975 --> 01:31:09,431
Get new canvas aloft!
升起新的帆布！

1001
01:31:10,270 --> 01:31:13,555
All hands, tend sails!
全体船员，收帆!

1002
01:31:13,648 --> 01:31:15,272
Aye, aye, sir.
是，是，长官

1003
01:31:15,566 --> 01:31:16,942
Get aloft.
把帆升起来

1004
01:31:18,903 --> 01:31:20,611
They'll trammel under!
他们在下面会挡住帆的！

1005
01:31:27,077 --> 01:31:29,912
Aloft with ye! Aloft!
你们都上去，上去！

1006
01:31:33,333 --> 01:31:35,870
Get up there! Get aloft!
爬到上面去，把帆升起来！

1007
01:32:24,129 --> 01:32:27,829
Captain, we cannot get more canvas up
in this wind!
船长，在这么大的风里，我们不能再增加帆了!

1008
01:32:27,924 --> 01:32:29,122
We must!
我们必须这么做

1009
01:32:36,098 --> 01:32:38,137
She won't come up!
这行不通的！

1010
01:32:52,086 --> 01:32:53,462
The masts!
桅杆！

1011
01:32:54,005 --> 01:32:56,756
Cut them away! Cut!
把他们砍断，砍断！

1012
01:32:56,841 --> 01:32:59,925
It's away with the masts, or we capsize!
要不把桅杆砍断，我们就要翻船了!

1013
01:33:06,683 --> 01:33:09,518
The masts! Cut the masts!
桅杆，切断桅杆！

1014
01:33:53,976 --> 01:33:55,553
Let fall.
放下

1015
01:33:57,479 --> 01:33:59,637
Let fall, I say.
我说，放下

1016
01:34:00,440 --> 01:34:03,275
I'll run you through.
我要把你扎个透心凉

1017
01:34:25,604 --> 01:34:27,596
St. Elmo's fire!
圣艾尔摩之火

1018
01:34:28,857 --> 01:34:30,600
Have mercy on us!
可怜可怜我们吧!

1019
01:34:31,818 --> 01:34:34,818
Aye, men!
是的，伙计们!

1020
01:34:37,031 --> 01:34:38,940
Mark it well.
好好记住

1021
01:34:40,159 --> 01:34:44,286
It lights our way to the white whale!
它照亮了我们通向莫比迪克的路!

1022
01:34:58,175 --> 01:35:01,544
Thus I put out...
就这样我放下了

1023
01:35:02,262 --> 01:35:05,216
the last fear.
最后的恐惧

1024
01:35:16,733 --> 01:35:18,144
Clear away!
收拾干净！

1025
01:35:18,485 --> 01:35:22,019
Raise new sail! We're running on!
升起新的帆布！ 我们继续前进！

1026
01:35:22,113 --> 01:35:24,818
Jump, my hearties! Jump now!
行动，我的伙伴们，立刻行动！

1027
01:35:29,787 --> 01:35:32,360
Where are the crew of the Pequod?
"裴廓德号"的船员在哪里?

1028
01:35:32,998 --> 01:35:36,201
There is not one face I know among 30.
30个人里没有一个人我还能认得出

1029
01:35:36,835 --> 01:35:38,993
He has snatched their souls.
他夺走了他们的灵魂。

1030
01:35:39,754 --> 01:35:42,327
Look at them. They are gloves.
看看他们。他们是傀儡

1031
01:35:42,548 --> 01:35:45,004
Ahab fills them. Ahab moves them.
亚哈支配它们。亚哈操纵它们。

1032
01:35:45,384 --> 01:35:49,334
You must admit, Mr. Starbuck,
he called that typhoon's bluff.
你得承认，斯达巴克先生
他接受了台风的挑战

1033
01:35:49,680 --> 01:35:54,591
Stood toe-to-toe with the bully,
traded blows with it till it hollered, "Help! "
和那恶霸面对面站着，互相痛殴，直到它大叫:“救命啊!”

1034
01:35:54,768 --> 01:35:58,302
Aye, man. And did you see
how he grabbed St. Elmo's fire by the tail?
啊,老兄。你看到他是怎么抓住圣埃尔莫之火的吗?

1035
01:35:58,396 --> 01:36:00,405
Only Ahab would do that.
只有亚哈才会那样做。

1036
01:36:01,707 --> 01:36:04,992
I see how madmen beget more madmen.
我看到疯子如何催生出更多的疯子。

1037
01:36:06,127 --> 01:36:08,962
Yet could I cure their madness now?
然而，我现在能治愈他们的疯狂吗?

1038
01:36:09,881 --> 01:36:11,708
Great God, where art thou?
伟大的上帝，你在哪里?

1039
01:36:12,049 --> 01:36:13,294
Shall l?
我可以吗？

1040
01:36:16,554 --> 01:36:18,297
Heave up!
起锚！

1041
01:36:19,848 --> 01:36:21,223
Avast!
停！

1042
01:36:45,705 --> 01:36:48,456
It's a mild day, Starbuck.
那是在风和日丽的一天，斯达巴克

1043
01:36:48,541 --> 01:36:50,580
Mild-looking sky.
天色看着很好

1044
01:36:52,836 --> 01:36:55,588
On such a day, I struck my first whale.
在那样的一天，我捕到了我的第一条鲸鱼。

1045
01:36:56,048 --> 01:36:59,251
A boy harpooneer. Forty, aye.
一个少年鱼叉手，四十年，是啊

1046
01:37:00,260 --> 01:37:04,091
Forty years and a thousand lowerings ago.
四十年过去了，我也上千次下到小艇里

1047
01:37:06,432 --> 01:37:09,184
Why this madness of the chase...
为什么这种疯狂的追逐…

1048
01:37:09,268 --> 01:37:12,387
this boiling blood and smoking brow?
这沸腾的血和冒烟的眉毛?

1049
01:37:12,896 --> 01:37:17,107
Why palsy the arm at the oar,
the iron, and the lance?
为什么要用桨、铁和长矛把胳膊累到瘫痪呢?

1050
01:37:21,112 --> 01:37:25,109
I feel old, Starbuck, and bowed.
我觉得自己老了，斯达巴克，直不起腰来

1051
01:37:26,992 --> 01:37:28,784
As though I were Adam...
仿佛我是亚当，

1052
01:37:29,453 --> 01:37:32,572
staggering under the piled centuries...
在天堂之后的几百年里

1053
01:37:32,789 --> 01:37:34,829
since paradise.
蹒跚前行

1054
01:37:39,597 --> 01:37:42,936
Stand close, Starbuck. Close to me.
站近点, 斯达巴克。离我近点。

1055
01:37:43,023 --> 01:37:45,561
Let me look into a human eye.
让我看看人类的眼睛。

1056
01:37:47,527 --> 01:37:50,978
It is better than to gaze into sea or sky.
它比凝视大海或天空要好。

1057
01:37:59,162 --> 01:38:02,994
Captain, now for the last time, I ask thee,
I implore thee...
船长，我最后一次问你，
我恳求你……

1058
01:38:03,375 --> 01:38:06,161
Iet us fly these deadly waters.
Let us home.
让我们离开这片危险的水域，我们回家吧

1059
01:38:07,086 --> 01:38:11,084
Have they not such mild blue days
even as this in old New Bedford?
即使在以前的新贝德福德，天气也不像现在这样好吗?

1060
01:38:14,927 --> 01:38:16,670
What is it?
究竟是什么？

1061
01:38:18,263 --> 01:38:22,723
What nameless, inscrutable,
unearthly thing...
什么无名、神秘、不可思议的东西……

1062
01:38:24,352 --> 01:38:28,848
commands me against all human lovings
and longings...
命令我去对抗所有人类的爱和渴望……

1063
01:38:30,024 --> 01:38:34,235
to keep pushing and crowding
and jamming myself on all the time...
不停地推呀挤呀，把自己塞得满满的……

1064
01:38:35,070 --> 01:38:38,439
making me do
what in my own natural heart...
让我去做那些依我的本性

1065
01:38:38,531 --> 01:38:40,654
I dare not dream of doing?
做梦都不敢去做的事情?

1066
01:38:41,784 --> 01:38:43,991
Is Ahab, Ahab?
亚哈还是那个亚哈吗？

1067
01:38:44,579 --> 01:38:48,362
Is it l, God, or who...
是我，上帝，还是谁…

1068
01:38:48,457 --> 01:38:50,331
that lifts this arm?
举起的这条胳膊

1069
01:38:51,710 --> 01:38:54,379
But if the great sun cannot move...
但是如果没有神那不可见的力量

1070
01:38:54,504 --> 01:38:56,876
except by God's invisible power...
连太阳都动不了的话

1071
01:38:58,550 --> 01:39:00,756
how can my small heart beat...
我的小心脏怎么能跳动……

1072
01:39:01,636 --> 01:39:03,842
my brain think thoughts...
我的大脑怎么会思考……

1073
01:39:04,472 --> 01:39:08,303
unless God does that beating,
does that thinking...
除非是神让心跳动，让大脑思考……

1074
01:39:08,433 --> 01:39:09,892
does that living...
让我活着

1075
01:39:10,477 --> 01:39:12,386
and not l?
而不是

1076
01:39:15,398 --> 01:39:17,355
By heavens, man...
伙计，是上天

1077
01:39:18,484 --> 01:39:22,284
we are turned round and round
in this world...
让我们在这世界上兜兜转转

1078
01:39:23,922 --> 01:39:26,413
Like yonder windlass...
就像那个绞盘一样……

1079
01:39:26,549 --> 01:39:29,466
and fate is the handspike.
而命运就是那根绞盘棒。

1080
01:39:30,595 --> 01:39:34,212
And all the time, that smiling sky...
一直以来，那微笑的天空……

1081
01:39:35,808 --> 01:39:38,642
and this unsounded sea.
这片寂静的大海。

1082
01:39:39,936 --> 01:39:42,427
Look ye into its deeps...
看看它的深处……

1083
01:39:42,814 --> 01:39:46,348
and see the everlasting slaughter
that goes on.
看那永无休止的杀戮。

1084
01:39:46,442 --> 01:39:50,855
Who put it into its creatures
to chase and fang one another?
是谁把它放进它自己的造物里，让它们互相追逐撕咬?

1085
01:39:51,572 --> 01:39:53,897
Where do murderers go, man?
杀人犯们都去哪了，伙计?

1086
01:39:54,950 --> 01:39:56,278
Who's to doom...
当法官自己被拖到律师面前时，

1087
01:39:56,368 --> 01:39:59,950
when the judge himself
is dragged before the bar?
谁会倒霉呢?

1088
01:40:02,665 --> 01:40:05,121
But it is a mild day...
但这是个风和日丽的日子

1089
01:40:05,876 --> 01:40:08,083
and a mild-looking sky.
天色看着很好

1090
01:40:13,967 --> 01:40:15,627
What ails you, Starbuck?
你怎么了，斯达巴克

1091
01:40:18,471 --> 01:40:20,380
Why do you tremble so?
你为什么抖得这么厉害?

1092
01:40:21,891 --> 01:40:24,512
Because I do not have the bowels
to slaughter thee...
因为我不忍心杀了你……

1093
01:40:24,602 --> 01:40:28,302
and save the whole ship's company
from being dragged to doom.
这样可以拯救整艘船的同伴，使他们免于被拖入厄运。

1094
01:40:30,023 --> 01:40:32,810
I plainly see my miserable office:
在反抗的过程中，我清楚地看到我那悲惨的职责:

1095
01:40:33,193 --> 01:40:34,984
to obey, rebelling.
服从

1096
01:40:36,321 --> 01:40:39,405
Worse still, to help thee
to thine impious end.
更糟的是，帮助你达到你那不虔诚的目的。

1097
01:40:40,950 --> 01:40:43,986
Starbuck, ye are tied to me.
斯达巴克，你和我是绑在一起的

1098
01:40:44,995 --> 01:40:47,320
This act is immutably decreed.
这项法令是不可更改的。

1099
01:40:48,248 --> 01:40:50,704
It was rehearsed by ye and me...
在一百万年前大海还没有形成的时候，

1100
01:40:51,793 --> 01:40:54,710
a billion years before this ocean rolled.
我和你就已经演练过了。

1101
01:41:04,112 --> 01:41:05,357
The air.
在空气里

1102
01:41:09,033 --> 01:41:12,069
Do you smell it, lads,
what the wind carries?
你们闻到了吗，伙计们，风里面夹杂的味道?

1103
01:41:16,623 --> 01:41:18,117
It smells like land.
像是陆地的味道

1104
01:41:18,208 --> 01:41:19,832
-Like an island. 像是一座岛
-Aye. 是的

1105
01:41:19,918 --> 01:41:22,872
A coral reef, green moss, shells...
珊瑚礁、青苔、贝壳……

1106
01:41:23,004 --> 01:41:26,503
bits and pieces
from all the oceans he ever swam through.
他游过的所有海洋的碎片。

1107
01:41:26,591 --> 01:41:29,377
An island to himself is the white whale.
白鲸就是一座独属于他自己的岛屿

1108
01:41:30,719 --> 01:41:31,834
Elijah.
以利亚

1109
01:41:34,097 --> 01:41:35,722
What say you, lad?
你说呢，小伙子?

1110
01:41:36,308 --> 01:41:38,680
The day we sailed, a man....
我们航行的那天，一个男人……

1111
01:41:39,477 --> 01:41:41,102
Elijah, his name was.
他的名字叫以利亚

1112
01:41:41,562 --> 01:41:43,555
-Well? 什么？
-He said.... 他说

1113
01:41:44,732 --> 01:41:46,974
He said, "A day will come at sea...
他说 “在海上，总有一天

1114
01:41:47,067 --> 01:41:49,854
"when you smell land
where there be no land.
“你会在没有陆地的地方闻到陆地的气味

1115
01:41:50,571 --> 01:41:53,571
"And on that day,
Ahab will go to his grave.
到那日，亚哈必死

1116
01:41:55,075 --> 01:41:58,739
"But he will rise again and beckon.
但他会再次起身并且招手

1117
01:42:00,246 --> 01:42:01,705
"And then all...
然后所有的人，

1118
01:42:06,668 --> 01:42:08,875
"all, save one, shall follow."
除了一个之外，都将追随他的命运

1119
01:42:13,133 --> 01:42:14,959
There she blows!
鲸鱼喷水！

1120
01:42:25,435 --> 01:42:26,764
Look.
看啊

1121
01:42:30,357 --> 01:42:33,393
Mastheaders, the birds mark the place.
桅顶岗哨，

1122
01:42:33,818 --> 01:42:35,478
Watch the birds!
注意海鸟！

1123
01:42:36,362 --> 01:42:38,319
Helmsman, luff a point.
舵手，转舵。

1124
01:42:39,752 --> 01:42:41,250
Stand by the boats!
小艇待命！

1125
01:42:41,383 --> 01:42:43,209
Down topgallants!
放下上桅帆!

1126
01:42:43,301 --> 01:42:45,756
-Same old bet, Stubb? 还是老的赌注，斯塔布？
-Aye. 好的

1127
01:42:54,102 --> 01:42:55,894
No, Pip. Stay on board.
不,皮普。呆在船上。

1128
01:42:55,979 --> 01:42:59,430
You be captain in my absence.
Stand ye there on the deck in my place.
我不在时你当队长。你站到甲板上我的位置那里。

1129
01:42:59,524 --> 01:43:01,148
Lower away!
放下小艇！

1130
01:43:06,989 --> 01:43:08,483
I'm Captain Pip.
我是皮普船长

1131
01:43:10,034 --> 01:43:12,275
Did you see him, men?
你们看见他了吗，伙计们?

1132
01:43:12,494 --> 01:43:16,491
Did you see his hump?
Like a great snow hill.
你看到他的驼峰了吗?像一座巨大的雪山。

1133
01:43:16,998 --> 01:43:19,536
Did you see the way he slides along?
你看到他滑行的样子了吗?

1134
01:43:20,168 --> 01:43:22,789
There's majesty for you.
这就是你的威严。

1135
01:43:23,004 --> 01:43:24,462
Don't look.
别看

1136
01:43:25,131 --> 01:43:27,289
I'll look for you.
我去找你

1137
01:43:30,177 --> 01:43:32,668
Did you see the lances in his back?
你看到他背上的长矛了吗?

1138
01:43:33,471 --> 01:43:34,847
My lances.
我的长矛

1139
01:43:35,515 --> 01:43:36,760
Mine.
我的

1140
01:43:36,849 --> 01:43:38,925
Struck in him years ago.
很多年前扎上去的

1141
01:43:42,521 --> 01:43:44,146
That's my lads.
这就对了，小伙子们

1142
01:43:44,481 --> 01:43:46,355
Wrack the oars off.
把桨拧下来。

1143
01:43:46,650 --> 01:43:48,274
Lay into it.
躺进去

1144
01:43:48,527 --> 01:43:50,270
Pull there, boys!
划到那里去，孩子们！

1145
01:43:50,612 --> 01:43:53,185
Pull, you green-faced posies!
划呀，你们这些晕船的娘炮！

1146
01:43:55,700 --> 01:43:57,776
Long and strong, men.
用力划到底，伙计们

1147
01:43:57,868 --> 01:44:00,157
Shake your bones, men.
抖擞精神，伙计们

1148
01:44:00,329 --> 01:44:01,907
Break in two.
分成两队

1149
01:44:02,706 --> 01:44:05,279
Moby Dick, show your trump.
莫比迪克，拿出你的真本事吧

1150
01:44:05,667 --> 01:44:07,458
Blister your lungs!
涨破你的肺！

1151
01:44:07,711 --> 01:44:09,833
We'll dam off your blood for ye!
我们要为你止血！

1152
01:44:29,872 --> 01:44:31,414
Pull soft now.
现在慢点划

1153
01:44:41,090 --> 01:44:42,549
He's sounded.
他听见了 

1154
01:44:45,386 --> 01:44:46,631
Ship oars.
收桨

1155
01:45:52,155 --> 01:45:54,147
Rise now, ye white whale.
出来吧，你这白鲸。

1156
01:45:54,699 --> 01:45:56,987
Show us your crooked jaw.
让我们看看你弯曲的下巴。

1157
01:45:58,202 --> 01:46:00,839
Show us your wrinkled brow.
让我们看看你皱起的额头。

1158
01:46:02,847 --> 01:46:04,127
Rise.
出来吧

1159
01:46:07,142 --> 01:46:08,637
Those birds.
那些 海鸟

1160
01:46:11,605 --> 01:46:13,182
He rises!
他出来了！

1161
01:46:18,945 --> 01:46:20,024
In!
靠近！

1162
01:46:20,696 --> 01:46:23,318
In and after him!
靠近追上他！

1163
01:46:30,455 --> 01:46:31,653
Ride!
爬上去！

1164
01:46:57,730 --> 01:46:58,892
Pull in!
靠近!

1165
01:47:10,408 --> 01:47:12,151
Let the men go!
别管那些人！

1166
01:47:17,206 --> 01:47:19,412
Pull in, men! Closer!
靠近一点，伙计们！ 近一点

1167
01:47:19,500 --> 01:47:20,994
He'll not escape!
他逃不掉了！

1168
01:47:22,919 --> 01:47:26,418
Thunder in hell! What's wrong with ye?
地狱的雷电! 你怎么了?

1169
01:47:34,472 --> 01:47:36,215
Damn ye!
该死的!

1170
01:47:41,619 --> 01:47:45,451
Ye whale! Ye damned whale!
你这鲸鱼，你这该死的鲸鱼！

1171
01:48:57,354 --> 01:49:01,850
From hell's heart I stab at thee!
我从地狱之心向你刺去!

1172
01:49:02,192 --> 01:49:04,019
For hate's sake...
为了仇恨……

1173
01:49:04,861 --> 01:49:09,688
I spit my last breath at thee...
我向你吐尽最后一口气……

1174
01:49:09,866 --> 01:49:12,736
thou damned whale!
你这该死的鲸鱼!

1175
01:49:39,950 --> 01:49:43,699
Away, no more of this.
Back to the Pequod. No more of this.
别再这样了。回到"裴廓德号"。别再这样了。

1176
01:49:58,050 --> 01:49:59,924
You see? Do you see?
你看到了吗？你看到了吗？

1177
01:50:02,095 --> 01:50:03,554
Ahab beckons.
亚哈招手了

1178
01:50:04,014 --> 01:50:06,172
He's dead, but he beckons.
他死了，但他在招手。

1179
01:50:08,435 --> 01:50:10,557
In after him!
靠近追上他！

1180
01:50:12,605 --> 01:50:13,980
After him!
追上他！

1181
01:50:14,065 --> 01:50:15,310
After that devil?
追那个魔鬼？

1182
01:50:15,441 --> 01:50:17,729
Moby Dick's no devil. He's a whale.
莫比迪克不是魔鬼，他是一只鲸鱼

1183
01:50:17,818 --> 01:50:20,938
A monstrous big whale, aye,
but a whale, no more.
一只巨大的鲸鱼，是的，但也就是只鲸鱼而已。

1184
01:50:21,029 --> 01:50:22,938
And we're whaling men, no less.
我们也依然是捕鲸人。

1185
01:50:23,031 --> 01:50:25,736
We do not turn from whales. We kill them.
我们不会从鲸鱼面前逃走，我们要杀了他们

1186
01:50:25,825 --> 01:50:27,734
We'll kill Moby Dick!
我们要杀了莫比迪克!

1187
01:50:28,411 --> 01:50:29,656
Pull!
划啊！

1188
01:50:31,455 --> 01:50:34,160
Ye heard Mr. Starbuck, didn't ye?
你听见斯达巴克先生了吧？

1189
01:50:34,917 --> 01:50:36,292
Didn't ye?
听见了吗？

1190
01:50:37,044 --> 01:50:39,083
Be ye whaling men or no?
你们是捕鲸人吗？

1191
01:50:39,504 --> 01:50:41,829
Pull, ye sheep-heads. Pull!
划啊，你们这些蠢货，划啊！

1192
01:50:52,975 --> 01:50:55,726
Ye should not have come back,
ye grinning whale.
你不应该回来的，你这露齿狞笑的鲸鱼。

1193
01:50:55,811 --> 01:50:58,515
We're cutting new mouths
in ye to grin with.
我们给你切个新的嘴巴出来，让你笑

1194
01:54:04,305 --> 01:54:05,680
The coffin.
那口棺材

1195
01:54:06,557 --> 01:54:10,140
Drowned Queequeg's coffin
was my life buoy.
淹死的魁魁格的棺材是我的救生圈

1196
01:54:10,686 --> 01:54:12,595
For one whole day and night...
整整一天一夜

1197
01:54:12,688 --> 01:54:16,519
it sustained me
on that soft and dirge-like main.
它支撑着我在那柔软的、像挽歌一样的大海上航行。

1198
01:54:17,359 --> 01:54:19,103
Then a sail appeared.
然后出现了一艘船

1199
01:54:19,661 --> 01:54:21,328
It was the Rachel.
是瑞秋号

1200
01:54:22,212 --> 01:54:25,213
The Rachel,
who in her long melancholy search...
瑞秋号在寻找她失踪的孩子

1201
01:54:25,298 --> 01:54:27,836
for her missing children found...
那漫长而忧郁的过程中，

1202
01:54:28,551 --> 01:54:30,129
another orphan.
又找到了一个孤儿

1203
01:54:32,513 --> 01:54:34,221
The drama 's done.
戏演完了

1204
01:54:34,807 --> 01:54:36,764
All are departed away.
所有的人都走了。

1205
01:54:37,768 --> 01:54:39,926
The great shroud of the sea...
"裴廓德号"和它的船员们

1206
01:54:40,020 --> 01:54:42,974
rolls over the Pequod, her crew...
还有莫比迪克

1207
01:54:43,732 --> 01:54:45,226
and Moby Dick.
都被大海那巨大的裹尸布卷走了

1208
01:54:46,359 --> 01:54:49,526
I only am escaped, alone...
只有我一个人逃出来

1209
01:54:49,904 --> 01:54:51,528
to tell thee.
给你们讲这个故事

1210
